[td][zone=3521][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=3521 pins=360520]36, 52[/lightbox][/td][td]Zabra''Jin[/td][/tr]\n[/table]\n\n[/tab]\n\n[tab name=Northrend_(16)][minibox][h3]Legend[/h3]\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/Mapper/pin-blue.png border=0] [url=#no-a]Alliance[/url] (8)\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/Mapper/pin-red.png border=0] [url=#no-h]Horde[/url] (8)\n[/minibox]Note: Bonfires in Northrend don''t count towards any achievement.\n[map zone=-5]\n[pin x=21.7 y=54.9 type=3][b]Fizzcrank Airstrip[/b]\n[color=q]Borean Tundra[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=55.3 y=46 type=3][b]Windrunner''s Overlook[/b]\n[color=q]Crystalsong Forest[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=55.1 y=52.8 type=3][b]Wintergarde Keep[/b]\n[color=q]Dragonblight[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=68.3 y=59.2 type=3][b]Amberpine Lodge[/b]\n[color=q]Grizzly Hills[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=79.7 y=67.9 type=3][b]Fort Wildervar[/b]\n[color=q]Howling Fjord[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=24.3 y=44 type=3][b]River''s Heart[/b]\n[color=q]Sholazar Basin[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=58.9 y=37.2 type=3][b]K3[/b]\n[color=q]The Storm Peaks[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=66 y=41.9 type=3][b]The Argent Stand[/b]\n[color=q]Zul''Drak[/color][/pin]\n\n[pin x=20.5 y=52.4 type=2][b]Bor''gorok Outpost[/b]\n[color=q]Borean Tundra[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=56.3 y=42.5 type=2][b]Sunreaver''s Command[/b]\n[color=q]Crystalsong Forest[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=43.7 y=57.8 type=2][b]Agmar''s Hammer[/b]\n[color=q]Dragonblight[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=63.6 y=60.9 type=2][b]Conquest Hold[/b]\n[color=q]Grizzly Hills[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=76.1 y=67.1 type=2][b]Camp Winterhoof[/b]\n[color=q]Howling Fjord[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=24 y=42.5 type=2][b]River''s Heart[/b]\n[color=q]Sholazar Basin[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=58 y=36.1 type=2][b]K3[/b]\n[color=q]The Storm Peaks[/color][/pin]\n[pin x=67.2 y=45 type=2][b]The Argent Stand[/b]\n[color=q]Zul''Drak[/color][/pin]\n[/map]\n\n[h3 id=no-a][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon] (8)[/h3]\n\nThese are the Alliance bonfires located in Northrend. Honor them if you''re Alliance, or desecrate them otherwise.\n[pad]\n[table class=grid width=100%]\n[tr][td width=33%][b]Zone[/b][/td][td width=33% align=center][b]Coords[/b][/td][td][b]Location[/b][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=3537][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=3537 pins=550200]55, 20[/lightbox][/td][td]Fizzcrank Airstrip[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=2817][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=2817 pins=780750]78, 75[/lightbox][/td][td]Windrunner''s Overlook[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=65][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=65 pins=750440]75, 44[/lightbox][/td][td]Wintergarde Keep[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=394][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=394 pins=340610]34, 61[/lightbox][/td][td]Amberpine Lodge[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=495][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=495 pins=580160]58, 16[/lightbox][/td][td]Fort Wildervar[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=3711][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=3711 pins=470660]47, 66[/lightbox][/td][td]River''s Heart[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=67][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=67 pins=420870]42, 87[/lightbox][/td][td]K3[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=66][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=66 pins=410610]41, 61[/lightbox][/td][td]The Argent Stand[/td][/tr]\n[/table]\n\n[h3 id=no-h][icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon] (8)[/h3]\n\nThese are the Horde bonfires located in Northrend. Honor them if you''re Horde, or desecrate them otherwise.\n[pad]\n[table class=grid width=100%]\n[tr][td width=33%][b]Zone[/b][/td][td width=33% align=center][b]Coords[/b][/td][td][b]Location[/b][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=3537][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=3537 pins=510120]51, 12[/lightbox][/td][td]Bor''gorok Outpost[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=2817][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=2817 pins=800530]80, 53[/lightbox][/td][td]Sunreaver''s Command[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=65][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=65 pins=390480]39, 48[/lightbox][/td][td]Agmar''s Hammer[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=394][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=394 pins=190610]19, 61[/lightbox][/td][td]Conquest Hold[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=495][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=495 pins=480130]48, 13[/lightbox][/td][td]Camp Winterhoof[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=3711][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=3711 pins=470620]47, 62[/lightbox][/td][td]River''s Heart[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=67][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=67 pins=400860]40, 86[/lightbox][/td][td]K3[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][zone=66][/td][td align=center][lightbox=map zone=66 pins=430710]43, 71[/lightbox][/td][td]The Argent Stand[/td][/tr]\n[/table]\n\n[/tab]\n\n[/tabs]\n\n[pad]\n\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/midsummer-fire-festival/maypole.jpg float=right border=0]In addition to awarding easy gold and [item=23247], there are a number of player buffs that are available from the various festival fire locations.\n\n[h3]Ribbon Pole[/h3]\n\nAt each bonfire you will find a ribbon pole, which creates a colorful streamer to your hand and causes your character to twirl very quickly (such as the effect of [spell=1680]). In addition to being rather hilarious, you will gain the [spell=29175] buff which increases experience gain by 10% for 3 minutes, stacking 3 more minutes on for every 3 seconds you remain twirling at the ribbon pole. The buff stacks up to a one hour duration (after 1 minute of twirling) and can stack with rested experience, so get it while it''s hot! If a player throws a [item=23247] into a festival fire, all surrounding players will gain the [spell=46352] buff, granting +3% physical/spell critical strike and reflecting Fire damage to attackers for 1 hour, and scales with your player level.\n\nAs if that wasn''t enough, if you happen to be at a festival flame that has been extinguished and no longer burns, tossing a [item=23247] into it will grant a zone-wide buff [spell=45444] which gives your faction''s players a 30% chance to inflict 10 Fire damage on any melee, ranged, or spell attack, increasing by 10 Fire damage per level.\n\n[h2 id=lord-ahune]Boss: Lord Ahune[/h2]\n\n[url=npc=25740][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/midsummer-fire-festival/lordahune.jpg float=right border=0][/url]Starting with 2010''s edition of the festival, Blizzard has changed the way seasonal bosses are accessed. In previous years, a quest (typically) would lead you to a dungeon where you would find that event''s boss and were able to summon him a limited number of times via quests to farm rare, exotic items. This year, all seasonal boss encounters will be accessed through the [b]Dungeon Finder[/b] tool, with any related quests now being found inside of the dungeon. Players will instantly be teleported to the associated dungeon, which means no more long treks to out-of-the-way dungeons like Scarlet Monastery or Blackrock Depths!\n\nAny special items that dropped off a seasonal boss in addition to his normal drop table (such as mounts from [npc=36296] or [npc=23682]) will now only have a chance to drop from a loot bag which is awarded upon killing the boss for the first time per day (basically, the same way a Random Heroic Dungeon only awards [item=49426]. Players can only receive a single loot bag per day, but will be able to re-queue for the boss in order to farm the more ''domestic'' drops. It is unknown what sort of drop rates these bags will have, or if you will still earn reward gold for each subsequent kill (my guess is no, seems rather exploitable). This means no more hours upon hours of farming for the most rare of items - every player in the party will have a chance to get a rare item out of the loot bag only once per day!\n\n[npc=25740] can be queued via [url=quest=25484]this "quest"[/url] and upon his defeat you will receive [item=54536] and [money=198600] (at level 80).\n\n[h3]Normal Drops[/h3]\n\n[ul]\n[li][item=54806][/li]\n[li][item=54805][/li]\n[li][item=54801][/li]\n[li][item=54804][/li]\n[li][item=54803][/li]\n[li][item=54802][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3]Loot Bag Drops[/h3]\n\nIt is a mystery :o\n\nTip: Take a look at Lord Ahune''s [url=npc=25740]loot table[/url] from last year for other possible drops.\n\n[h2]Festival Camps[/h2]\n\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/midsummer-fire-festival/pavilion.jpg float=right border=0]The main festival camps can be found at the following locations:\n\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon]:[/b] [lightbox=map zone=141 pins=550910]Darnassus[/lightbox], [lightbox=map zone=1537 pins=640250]Ironforge[/lightbox], [lightbox=map zone=1519 pins=490720]Stormwind City[/lightbox] and [lightbox=map zone=3557 pins=410260]The Exodar[/lightbox][/li]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon]:[/b] [lightbox=map zone=1637 pins=470380]Orgrimmar[/lightbox], [lightbox=map zone=3487 pins=700430]Silvermoon City[/lightbox], [lightbox=map zone=1638 pins=210260]Thunder Bluff[/lightbox] and [lightbox=map zone=1497 pins=68090]Undercity[/lightbox][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3]Quests[/h3]\n\n[ul]\n[li][icon name=side_horde][b][quest=11971][/b][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][b][quest=11970][/b][/icon]\n[b]Start:[/b] [url=?search=commoner#npcs]"Commoner"[/url] NPCs in major cities.\n[b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=16818][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=16817][/icon]\nThese quests are simply "breadcrumb" quests given by flavor NPCs in major cities to alert you to the Festival''s start and to lead you to the Festival Fire camps. Awards a single [item=23247], and is turned in at the [icon name=side_horde][npc=16818][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=16817][/icon], who are found in their appropriate faction major cities (or [zone=3703]). This quest is [b]not[/b] required, and the NPC will give the next quest regardless of its completion.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=11966][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=11964][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=16818][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=16817][/icon]\n[b]End:[/b] [url=/?npc=26401]Summer Scorchling[/url]\nA quick and easy quest, simply talk to the NPC located near a Festival Fire in any major city to accept the quest and receive the [item=35725], then walk outside the city and turn it in at a [npc=25706] located near a festival fire. You can complete this quest at basically any of your faction''s fires, it doesn''t matter which one. The quest is ridiculously easy and awards only single [item=23247], but the short event following completion is quite a treat.[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h2]Torch Throwing[/h2]\n\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/midsummer-fire-festival/brazier.jpg float=right border=0]The [icon name=side_horde][npc=25975][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=26113][/icon] located near the bonfire offers a two-part quest chain which unlocks two daily quests that can be completed for gold as well as [item=23247].\n\n[h3]Quests[/h3]\n\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=11922][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=11731][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=26113][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=25975][/icon]\nYou must aim and throw [item=34862] at a series of braziers found nearby the questgiver. A brazier is only considered an active target when it has an arrow above it that looks like a [spell=14325]; non-marked braziers will not count towards the quest objective. When you use the torch you will be given a small targeting circle that you must place over an active brazier and click to toss. You are given x seconds to hit 8 targets, and if you are successful you are awarded with [item=23247] x5 and gold (and experience, if you are lower than 80).\n[pad]\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=11926][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=11921][/icon][/b] - Repeatable daily quest, awards [item=23247] x5.[/li][/ul]\n[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11923][/b] or [b][quest=11657][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=26113][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=25975][/icon]\nYou must light the [item=34833] at the bonfire, which will then toss a flaming torch into the air. You have to follow the shadow of the torch, and then wait where it will land to "catch" it. If you miss, but are near where it lands you will suffer fire damage which can add up pretty quick if you''re not yet used to the quest. When you catch the torch, there will be a very short delay before you will automatically toss it back up into the air, only this time it will travel a much shorter distance. You must "catch" the torch four times in a row to complete the quest, and you will be rewarded with [item=34599] x5 and [item=23247] x5.\n[pad]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11925][/b] or [b][quest=11924][/b] - Repeatable daily quest, awards [item=23247] x5.[/li][/ul]\n[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h2]Twilight Hammer[/h2]\n\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/midsummer-fire-festival/banner.jpg float=right border=0][b][color=q10]Please note:[/color][/b] These quest chains may have been removed in 2010 with the changes made to seasonal boss encounters. See the [url=#lord-ahune]Lord Ahune[/url] section for more information. I will be updating the information in this section as soon as possible.\n\n[h3]Quests[/h3]\n\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11886][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=26221]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=25324]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11891][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=25324]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=12012][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=25324]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=26221]\n[/li][/ul][/li][/ul][/li]\n[/ul]\n\nUpon completion of this quest chain, a repeatable daily quest will be accessible to players level 22 and above.  The quest you get is dependent on your current level.\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11917] (Level 22)[/b] - Repeatable daily quest, awards [item=23247] x10 and [b][money=350][/b][/li]\n[li][b][quest=11947] (Level 32)[/b] - Repeatable daily quest, awards [item=23247] x10 and [b][money=800][/b][/li]\n[li][b][quest=11948] (Level 43)[/b] - Repeatable daily quest, awards [item=23247] x10 and [b][money=1500][/b][/li]\n[li][b][quest=11952] (Level 51)[/b] - Repeatable daily quest, awards [item=23247] x10 and [b][money=1900][/b][/li]\n[li][b][quest=11953] (Level 60)[/b] - Repeatable daily quest, awards [item=23247] x10 and [b][money=2300][/b][/li]\n[li][b][quest=11954] (Level 67)[/b] - Repeatable daily quest, awards [item=23247] x10 and [b][money=9400][/b][/li]\n[/ul]\n\nFor players level 65 and above, an additional quest will become available. The first 2 parts of this quest chain are merely breadcrumb quests, intended to lead you to the next questgivers and [b]do not[/b] need to be completed in order to continue the chain. This means you can walk right into [zone=3717] and start the Ahune summoning chain without having done [i]any[/i] previous quest.\n\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11955][/b]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11696][/b]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11691][/b] - Repeatable daily quest, Awards [b][money=44000][/b] (+ [b][money=75900][/b] at level 80)[/li]\n[/ul][/li][/ul][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11972][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [item=35723], which drops from [npc=25740] on player''s first kill.\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=25697]\nUpon successfully killing Ahune for the first time, he will drop a quest item that you return to [url=?npc=25697]Luma Skymother[/url]. This quest cannot be completed more than once (this year) - which means you will have to choose one tabard per character! You will be rewarded with [item=23247] x20 and your choice of either the [item=35279] or the [item=35280][pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3][toggler id=twilight-hammer-detailed hidden]Detailed Information[/toggler][/h3]\n\n[div id=twilight-hammer-detailed hidden]At each major city capital camp there is an [npc=26221] representing the faction neutral Earthen Ring, an organization of shaman similar to the druids'' [faction=609]. The Elder will offers a short quest chain starting with [b][quest=11886][/b], for which you must travel to the Zoram Strand of [zone=331] and slay level 20+ [npc=25863] until the [item=35277] drops. Once you receive it, use the [item=35828] to summon an [npc=25324] to complete the quest. \n\nThe Guide will then give you the next part of the quest, [b][quest=11891][/b] for which you are given an orb that changes you into a Crawler for three minutes. In your new disguise, you must travel northwest of the entrance of [zone=719] - you will know you''re going the right way if you periodically find blue-flamed torches, and eventually a small encampment on the shore. While disguised, witness the exchange between the naga and the [npc=25949] until the quest completes. When it is finished, you can move out of range of the mobs and cancel the disguise, and summon the [npc=25324] once again. This time, upon relaying the information, the guide will give you the quest [b][quest=12012][/b], requesting that you return to an [npc=26221] and report your findings.\n\nOnce you have returned to an [npc=26221], the quest chain will complete and either one or two quests will become available, depending on your level. For characters level 22 and above, a [b]repeatable daily quest[/b] will open up. The quest is called [b]Striking Back[/b], and depending on your level range you will be given a single objective at a location in Azeroth or Outland.\n[ul]\n[li][quest=11917] (Level 22) - This quest has you summon and kill a [npc=26116] from an Ice Stone located at the Zoram Strand, [zone=331]. Awards [item=23247] x10 and [b]3 silver 50 copper[/b].[/li] \n[li][quest=11947] (Level 32) - This quest has you summon and kill a [npc=26178] from an Ice Stone at Ethel Rethor, [zone=405]. Awards [item=23247] x10 and [b]8 silver[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=11948] (Level 43) - This quest has you summon and kill a [npc=26204] from an Ice Stone in [zone=33]. Awards [item=23247] x10 and [b]15 silver[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=11952] (Level 51) - This quest has you summon and kill a [npc=26214] from an Ice Stone in the northwestern part of [zone=51]. Awards [item=23247] x10 and [b]19 silver[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=11953] (Level 60) - This quest has you summon and kill a [npc=26215] from an Ice Stone at Twilight''s Run, [zone=1377]. Awards [item=23247] x10 and [b]23 silver[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=11954] (Level 67) - This quest has you summon and kill a [npc=26216] from an Ice Stone near the Dark Portal, in [zone=3483]. Awards [item=23247] x10 and [b]94 silver[/b].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nIf you character is [b]level 65 or higher[/b], the [npc=26221] will offer a second quest, [b][quest=11955][/b]. This quest asks you to travel to the [zone=3717] in [zone=3521] in search of [npc=25710], who is located right inside the instance. This quest, and it''s follow-up, are [i]not actually required[/i] to summon Ahune! You can summon Ahune by going straight to Luma Skymother, without having completed any other Midsummer quest. \n\nWhen you turn in that quest she will give the quest [b][quest=11696][/b] and ask that you find [npc=25697], who is located a bit further into the instance. Finally, Luma will give you the quest [b][quest=11691][/b], granting you an [item=34953] allowing you to (you guessed it) summon [npc=25740]. Use the totem at the Ice Stone located just beyond Luma and defeat Ahune to complete the quest, which awards [b][money=44000][/b] and experience (or an additional [b][money=75900][/b] at level 80).\n\nIf this is your first time killing Ahune, he will drop an item called [item=35723] which starts the quest [b][quest=11972][/b]. Accept the quest and bring the shard to [npc=25697], and she will reward you with [item=23247] x20 and your choice of a unique tabard: the [item=35279] or the [item=35280]. You can only complete this quest [b]once[/b], so you [b]will not[/b] be able to receive both tabards on the same character (well, not until next year at least)![/div]\n\n[h2]Midsummer Festival Items[/h2]\n\nThere are [icon name=side_alliance][npc=26123]s[/icon] / [icon name=side_horde][npc=26124]s[/icon] located near each major city''s festival fire who sell a variety of nifty items in exchange for [item=23247]. \n\nMany of these items are required for various achievements, though it is worth mentioning that items can be "returned" within 2 hours for a full refund of the cost. This may come in handy for obtaining the achievement [achievement=271]!\n\n[pad]\n\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/midsummer-fire-festival/crate.jpg float=right border=0][table class=grid width=40%]\n[tr][td][b]Item[/b][/td][td align=center width=25%][b]Cost[/b][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][div float=right margin=0][small][i]Limited duration[/i][/small][/div][item=23246][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,2][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][div float=right margin=0][small][i]Limited duration[/i][/small][/div][item=34684][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,2][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][div float=right margin=0][small][i]Limited duration[/i][/small][/div][item=23215][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,5][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][div float=right margin=0][small][i]Limited duration[/i][/small][/div][item=23435][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,5][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][div float=right margin=0][small][i]Limited duration[/i][/small][/div][item=23327][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,5][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][div float=right margin=0][small][i]Limited duration[/i][/small][/div][item=23326][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,5][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][div float=right margin=0][small][i]Limited duration[/i][/small][/div][item=23211][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,5][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=23324][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,100][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=34685][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,100][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=34683][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,200][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=34686][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,350][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=23083][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=23247,350][/td][/tr]\n[/table]\n\n[h2]Achievements[/h2]\n\n[ul]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1039][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1038][/icon][/b]\nThis achievement can be found in the main World Events achievement category and is awarded upon completion of every one of the Midsummer Fire Festival achievements. This achievement awards the player title [icon name=side_horde]Flame Keeper[/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance]Flame Warden[/icon] (depending on faction) and is a requirement towards completion of [icon name=side_horde][achievement=2145][/icon] ([icon name=side_alliance][achievement=2144][/icon]) which rewards the beautiful [spell=60024].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=271][/b]\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/midsummer-fire-festival/flag.jpg float=right border=0]To earn this achievement you have to dance at a ribbon pole located near festival Bonfires for a full minute while wearing the full [url=/?itemset=785]Midsummer Reveler[/url] set. You will need a total of 400 [item=23247] to purchase all three pieces - 100 for the [item=23324], 100 for [item=34685] and 200 for [item=34683]. Please note that the [item=23323] obtained from the Thief''s Reward quests is not required for this achievement. Simply right click a ribbon pole to grab a ribbon and start spinning![pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1037][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1035][/icon][/b]\nThis achievement is awarded upon completion of all three of the Extinguishing meta achievements available to each faction.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1032][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1029][/icon][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must extinguish all of the opposing faction''s flames found on the continent of Kailmdor. A full list of these bonfires can be found above.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1031][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1028][/icon][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must extinguish all of the opposing faction''s flames found on the continent of Eastern Kingdoms. A full list of these bonfires can be found above.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1033][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1030][/icon][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must extinguish all of the opposing faction''s flames found on the continent of Outland. A full list of these bonfires can be found above.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1036][/icon][/b] or The [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1034][/icon][/b]\nThis achievement is awarded upon completion of all three of the [icon name=side_horde]Flame Keeper[/icon] / [icon name=side_alliance]Flame Warden[/icon] meta achievements available to each faction.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1025][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1022][/icon][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must honor all of your faction''s flames found on the continent of Eastern Kingdoms. A full list of these bonfires can be found above.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1026][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1023][/icon][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must honor all of your faction''s flames found on the continent of Kalimdor. A full list of these bonfires can be found above.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1027][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1024][/icon][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must honor all of your faction''s flames found on the continent of Outland. A full list of these bonfires can be found above.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1145][/b]\nTo obtain this achievement you must complete the quest [quest=9339] ([url=/?quest=9365]Alliance[/url]), which requires you to sneak into the four major cities of your opposing faction to ''steal'' their festival flames. Details on stealing the flames can be found above.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=263][/b]\nTo obtain this achievement you must defeat [npc=25740] who can be summoned inside [zone=3717] of [zone=3905], in [zone=3521]. Players who participated in last year''s Midsummer festivities may find that they have already earned this achievement, among others. Details on summoning Lord Ahune can be found above.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=272][/b]\nFor this achievement, purchase at least 10 [item=34599] from a Midsummer vendor, and juggle them 40 times within 15 seconds while in Dalaran. Hotkey the torches and click the ground below your character to juggle them in place, though be careful as Dalaran''s lag may be a bit unforgiving![/li]\n[/ul]'),
    (300,5,0,'childrens-week','[menu tab=6 path=6,3,childrens-week]\n\nChildren''s Week is a week in which we brave face a challenge greater than any undead monstrosity, a task more daunting than saving the world. We must become parents for all those orphans throughout Azeroth and make sure they are happy. We can''t tank a child''s fears, we can''t heal its memories of pain, nor can we DPS the sorrow out of them. So equip your toys, make a mage conjure a candy table, fill your quiver with joy, load your gun with something colorful, and venture into the World of Parenting!\n\n[div class=minibox style="text-align:left;  clear:right"][toc][/div]\n\n[h2]Companions[/h2]\n\nThe quest chains listed in this guide reward the following companion pets. You can get 1 pet from each chain per year.\n\n[b]Orgrimmar/Stormwind[/b]\n\n[ul]\n[li][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/childrens-week/elekk.jpg float=right border=0][item=23007][/li]\n[li][item=23015][/li]\n[li][item=23002][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[b]Shattrath (Outland)[/b]\n\n[ul]\n[li][item=32616][/li]\n[li][item=32622][/li]\n[li][item=32617][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[b]Dalaran (Northrend)[/b]\n\n[ul]\n[li][item=46545][/li]\n[li][item=46544][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h2 clear=both][icon name=side_horde]Horde Quests[/icon][/h2]\n\nThere are two orphans that Horde players can adopt during Children''s Week, each with different quests. You can adopt both orphans (at the same time, even) and complete both quest chains and obtain two cute pets per year!\n\n[h3][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/childrens-week/orphan-orc.jpg float=right border=0][icon name=race_orc_male]Orcish Orphan (Grunth)[/icon][/h3]\nYou can adopt an Orcish orphan in [zone=1637] by speaking with [npc=14451] and accepting her quest, [quest=172]. Use the [item=18597] to summon your orphan, Grunth, and complete this quest.\n\nOnce you have completed this quest, three new quests become available from your orphan:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=1800]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the [zone=1497]''s Throne Room. This quest awards [money=13200] at 80 and [b]75 Horde reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=910]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the docks of Ratchet, in [zone=17]. This quest awards [money=13200] at 80 and [b]75 Horde reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=911]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the [lightbox=map zone=17 pins=483067]Mor''shan Rampart[/lightbox], at the very northern exit of [zone=17]. This quest awards [money=13200] at 80 and [b]75 Horde reputation[/b].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nUpon completion of all three of these quests, two new quests will become available:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=4822]\nFor this quest, you must purchase [item=7228] for your orphan. This item can be purchased from [npc=14480], a seasonal goblin vendor found near the bank in [zone=1637], from a [npc=24934] located downstairs in the old world Zeppelin or from [npc=6496] in [zone=400]. This quest awards [money=13200] at 80 and [b]150 Horde reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=925]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan out to [zone=1638] and obtain [item=18643] from [npc=3057]. This quest awards [money=13200] at 80 and [b]150 Horde reputation[/b].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nFinally, you will be given a quest to return the orphan whistle to the Matron:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=5502]\nReturn the Orcish Orphan the Matron in Orgrimmar and you will be given your choice of one from the following cute pets:\n[ul]\n[li][item=23007][/li]\n[li][item=23015][/li]\n[li][item=23002][/li]\n[/ul]\nOr, if you hate pets, you can opt to select the [item=23022], which contains a measly [money=50000]. This quest awards [money=33000] at 80 and [b]500 Horde reputation[/b]! You will have the option to complete this quest again next year, so you can eventually collect all of the pets![/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[hr]\n\n[h3][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/childrens-week/orphan-bloodelf.jpg float=right border=0][icon name=race_bloodelf_female]Blood Elf Orphan (Salandria)[/icon][/h3]\nYou can adopt an Blood Elf orphan in [zone=3703] by speaking with [npc=22819] and accepting her quest, [quest=10942]. Use the [item=31880] to summon your orphan, Salandria, and complete this quest.\n\nOnce you have completed this quest, three new quests become available from your orphan:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=10945]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to Sporeggar, in [zone=3521] and speak with [npc=22823]. This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]250 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=10953]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the Throne of the Elements, in [zone=3518], and speak with [npc=18072]. This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]250 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=10951]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the Stair of Destiny before the Dark Portal, in [zone=3483]. Speak to your orphan once the quest objective has completed to turn in this quest. This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]250 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nUpon completion of all three of these quests, two new quests will become available:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=11975]\nFor this quest, take your orphan to see The Tauren Chieftians, located up on a balcony at the Walk of Elders, in [zone=3487]. This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]250 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=10963]\nFor this quest, take your orphan out to the Caverns of Time and bring her up to the platform where [npc=19934] lies. On your way out, purchase a [item=31951] from [npc=21643], the Keepers of Time Quartermaster, to complete this quest. This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]250 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nFinally, you will be given a quest to return the orphan whistle to the Matron:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=10967]\nReturn the Blood Elf Orphan the Matron in [zone=3703] and you will be given your choice of one from the following cute pets:\n[ul]\n[li][item=32616][/li]\n[li][item=32622][/li]\n[li][item=32617][/li]\n[/ul]\nYou will have the option to complete this quest again next year, so you can eventually collect all of the pets! This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]500 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h2][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance Quests[/icon][/h2]\n\nThere are two orphans that Alliance players can adopt during Children''s Week, each with different quests. You can adopt both orphans (at the same time, even) and complete both quest chains and obtain two cute pets per year!\n\n[h3][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/childrens-week/orphan-human.jpg float=right border=0][icon name=race_human_male]Human Orphan (Randis)[/icon][/h3]\nYou can adopt an Human orphan in [zone=1519] by speaking with [npc=14450] and accepting her quest, [quest=1468]. Use the [item=18598] to summon your orphan, Randis, and complete this quest.\n\nOnce you have completed this quest, three new quests become available from your orphan:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=1687]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the Westfall Lighthouse (of [npc=392] fame) in [zone=40]. This quest awards [money=13200] at 80 and [b]75 Alliance reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=1558]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the Stonewrought Dam in [zone=38]. This quest awards [money=13200] at 80 and [b]75 Alliance reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=1479]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the bank in [zone=1657]. This quest awards [money=13200] at 80 and [b]75 Alliance reputation[/b].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nUpon completion of all three of these quests, two new quests will become available:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=4822]\nFor this quest, you must purchase [item=7228] for your orphan. This item can be purchased from [npc=14481], a seasonal pink-haired gnomish vendor found in [zone=1519], [npc=18914] in Telaar, [zone=3518] or [npc=6496] in [zone=400]. Alliance players are able to interact with the [npc=24934] though it may be a bit tricky to get to. This quest awards [money=13200] at 80 and [b]150 Alliance reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=558]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan out to Theramore, in [zone=15], and obtain [item=18642] from [npc=4968]. This quest awards [money=13200] at 80 and [b]150 Alliance reputation[/b].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nFinally, you will be given a quest to return the orphan whistle to the Matron:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=171]\nReturn the Human Orphan the Matron in [zone=1519] and you will be given your choice of one from the following cute pets:\n[ul]\n[li][item=23007][/li]\n[li][item=23015][/li]\n[li][item=23002][/li]\n[/ul]\nOr, if you hate pets, you can opt to select the [item=23022], which contains a measly [money=50000]. This quest awards [money=33000] at 80 and [b]500 Alliance reputation[/b]! You will have the option to complete this quest again next year, so you can eventually collect all of the pets![/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[hr]\n\n[h3][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/childrens-week/orphan-draenei.jpg float=right border=0][icon name=race_draenei_female]Draenei Orphan (Dornaa)[/icon][/h3]\nYou can adopt an Draenei orphan in [zone=3703] by speaking with [npc=22819] and accepting her quest, [quest=10943]. Use the [item=31881] to summon your orphan, Dornaa, and complete this quest.\n\nOnce you have completed this quest, three new quests become available from your orphan:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=10950]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan out to the meeting stone at the Ring of Observance at the center of [zone=3519] and aid her in summoning an [npc=23133]. This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]250 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=10954]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan out to Aeris Landing in [zone=3518], and speak with her brother, [npc=22836]. This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]250 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=10952]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the Stair of Destiny before the Dark Portal, in [zone=3483]. Speak to your orphan once the quest objective has completed to turn in this quest. This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]250 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nUpon completion of all three of these quests, two new quests will become available:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=10956]\nFor this quest, you must take your orphan to see [npc=17538] at the Seat of the Naaru in [zone=3557]. He will then give you another quest, [quest=10968], which asks that you go out to visit [npc=17204] in [zone=3557]''s Crystal Hall. These two quests award a total of [b]125 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li]\n[li][quest=10962]\nFor this quest, take your orphan out to the Caverns of Time and bring her up to the platform where [npc=19934] lies. On your way out, purchase a [item=31951] from [npc=21643], the Keepers of Time Quartermaster, to complete this quest. This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]250 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nFinally, you will be given a quest to return the orphan whistle to the Matron:\n[ul]\n[li][quest=10966]\nReturn the Draenei Orphan the Matron in [zone=3703] and you will be given your choice of one from the following cute pets:\n[ul]\n[li][item=32616][/li]\n[li][item=32622][/li]\n[li][item=32617][/li]\n[/ul]\nYou will have the option to complete this quest again next year, so you can eventually collect all of the pets! This quest awards [money=132300] at 80 and [b]500 Lower City reputation[/b].[/li][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h2]Neutral Quests[/h2]\n\nIf this is your first year doing the Northrend Children''s Week quests, you can choose to sponsor either of these 2 unfortunate orphans by talking to [npc=34365] in [zone=4395]. You can only pick one or the other orphan to adopt, so choose wisely as you will have to wait until next year to obtain the other pet!\n\n[h3][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/childrens-week/orphan-oracle.jpg float=right border=0]Oracle Orphan (Roo)[/h3]\n\n[ul]\n[li][quest=13926][ul]\n[li][quest=13929]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the great tree Grizzlemaw, located in [zone=394].[/li]\n[li][quest=13933]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the Bronze Dragonshrine, located in [zone=65].[/li]\n[li][quest=13950]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the Winterfin Retreat, located in [zone=3537].[/li]\n[li][quest=13956]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to visit [npc=28092] at the Shaper''s Terrace in [zone=490], which can [b]only[/b] be reached via the Waygate located in [zone=3711].[/li]\n[li][quest=13954]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to visit [npc=26917], found at the top of Wyrmrest Temple in [zone=65].[/li]\n[/ul][/li]\n[li][quest=13937]\nFor this quest, you must purchase a [item=46693] from the Wonderworks in [zone=4395], then throw it to your orphan. Please note that this is a special, event only item and should not be confused with the [item=34498] sold year-round.[/li]\n[li][quest=13959]\nFinally, simply return your orphan to [npc=34365] in [zone=4395]. Upon completion of this quest, [item=46545] will be mailed to you.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[hr]\n\n[h3][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/childrens-week/orphan-wolvar.jpg float=right border=0]Wolvar Orphan (Kekek)[/h3]\n\n[ul]\n[li][quest=13927][ul]\n[li][quest=13930]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the great tree Grizzlemaw, located in [zone=394].[/li]\n[li][quest=13934]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the Bronze Dragonshrine, located in [zone=65].[/li]\n[li][quest=13951]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to the Snowfall Glade, located in [zone=65].[/li]\n[li][quest=13955]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to visit [npc=26917], found at the top of Wyrmrest Temple in [zone=65].[/li]\n[li][quest=13957]\nFor this quest, bring your orphan to visit [npc=27986], found at the Nesingwary Base Camp in [zone=3711].[/li]\n[/ul][/li]\n[li][quest=13938]\nFor this quest, you must purchase a [item=46693] from the Wonderworks in [zone=4395], then throw it to your orphan. Please note that this is a special, event only item and should not be confused with the [item=34498] sold year-round.[/li]\n[li][quest=13960]\nFinally, simply return your orphan to [npc=34365] in [zone=4395]. Upon completion of this quest, [item=46544] will be mailed to you.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h2]Achievements[/h2]\n\n[ul]\n[li][b][achievement=1793][/b]\nThis achievement can be found in the main World Events achievement category and is awarded upon completion of every one of the Children''s Week achievements [i]except[/i] [achievement=275]. This achievement awards the player title [b]''Matron''[/b] or [b]''Patron''[/b] (depending on character gender) and is a requirement towards completion of [achievement=2145] ([url=?achievement=2144]Alliance version[/url]) which rewards the beautiful [item=44177].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1792][/b]\nFor this achievement, simply complete one of the Orphan quest chains (as detailed above) and obtain a cute pet! Any pet will count towards this achievement, and you may already have it if you''ve compeleted Children''s Week quest chain in the past.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1788][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must eat each of the delicious (and unhealthy) foods listed while your orphan is out:\n[ul]\n[li][item=7228] - Sold by [url=/?item=7228]these vendors[/url] (Note that not all are currently in-game!)[/li]\n[li][item=42429] - Sold by [npc=29548], in [zone=4395][/li]\n[li][item=42434] - Sold by [npc=29548], in [zone=4395] (Purchase a [item=42438], or take a slice from a party member''s)[/li]\n[li][item=42430] - Sold by [npc=29548], in [zone=4395][/li]\n[li][item=43490] - Crafted by [spell=58512][/li]\n[li][item=33924] - Crafted by [spell=43779][/li]\n[li][item=42431] - Sold by [npc=29548], in [zone=4395][/li]\n[/ul]\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1789][/b]\nFor this achievement, simply complete any five daily quests while your orphan is out. You do not have to have an Orphan while actually doing the quests, you can instead opt to simply summon your ward before turning a quest in.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1790][/b]\nFor this achievement, head out to [zone=1196] and defeat [npc=26861] with your orphan out. This achivement can be completed with either Orphan out, and both Normal and Heroic difficulty.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1791][/b]\nFor this achievement, simply use your [item=6948] while your orphan is out.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1786][/b]\nThis is one of the trickier Children''s Week achievements. For this achievement, you must complete each of these four objectives in PVP battlegrounds while your orphan is out:\n[ul]\n[li]Capture the flag in [zone=3820][/li]\n[li]Assault a tower in [zone=2597][/li]\n[li]Assault a flag in [zone=3358][/li]\n[li]Return a fallen flag in [zone=3277][/li]\n[/ul][pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=275][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must obtain all three of the [zone=3703] non-combat pets on one character. This achievement is [i]not[/i] required for the meta achievement [achievement=1793], thankfully, as it takes three years of Children''s Week questing to complete.[/li]\n[/ul]'),
    (300,6,0,'brewfest','[menu tab=6 path=6,3,brewfest]\n\n[div class="minibox minibox-left" style="text-align:left"][toc][/div]\n\n[h2 clear=both]Brewfest Quests![/h2]\n[ul]\n[li][b]Welcome to Brewfest![/b]\nAvailable from [icon name=side_horde][npc=24711][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=24710][/icon], which will award a single brew.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde]Another Year, Another Souvenir.[/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance]Another Year, Another Souvenir.[/icon][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=24510][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=24468][/icon]\n[b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=24495][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23710][/icon]\nDon''t forget to pick up your honorary Brewfest souvenir! Please note that you must first complete [b][icon name=side_horde][quest=11409][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=11318][/icon][/b] before this quest will become available. Once you have done so, speak to either [icon name=side_horde][npc=24510][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=24468][/icon] to receive your voucher, and turn it in at your faction''s Brewfest token redeemer. Unfortunately, you will receive the same Brewfest souvenir as last year, a [item=37892], and will even be awarded last year''s Feat of Strength! Anyway, fill it up at any keg with brew, or just beat things upside the head with it!\n[pad]\n[/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=12191][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=12022][/icon][/b] -  Awards 10 [item=37829]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=27216][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=27215][/icon]\nThis quest is ridiculously easy; simply accept the quest, loot a [item=33096] from the nearby tables, target [npc=24108] and use the brew. Do this five times, then turn around and accept your tokens.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=11431][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=11117][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=24657][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23486][/icon]\nFor this quest, you must use the provided [item=32907] to capture 5 stunned Wolpertingers, which can be found running around and outside the Brewfest main festival camp grounds. In order to see the Wolpertingers, you must either be incredibly drunk off any alcoholic beverage or wearing the [item=46735], available from the questgiver by request. Manage to net 5 Wolpertingers and turn in the quest to be rewarded with a Wolpertinger of your own - encased in a [item=32233]![pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=11120][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=11118][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=24657][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23486][/icon]\nFor this quest, players must travel to the specified locations and use the provided [item=32960] to "slay" three pink Elekk hallucinations at each location. In order to see the Elekks, you must either be incredibly drunk off any alcoholic beverage or wearing the [item=46735], available from the questgiver by request. Horde players will have to visit [zone=3430], [zone=215] and [zone=85] and Alliance players will have to visit [zone=3524], [zone=12], and [zone=141].[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3][icon name=ability_mount_mountainram]Ram Racing Quests[/icon][/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=11409][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=11318][/icon][/b] - Does not award tokens, but [b]unlocks the other ram riding dailies[/b].\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=24497][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23558][/icon]\nThis quest is intended to introduce players to the fine art of ram riding. Upon accepting this quest, [icon name=side_horde][npc=24497][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23558][/icon] will mount you upon one of his fine riding rams and give you the [item=33306], which you must use to control the speed of your ram. You have to maintain certain speeds for 8 seconds each, which is indicated not only by the movement speed of your ram but by colored buff icons on your player. Be careful not to travel too fast, or your ram will get fatigued and slow down severely! You can lower (or completely reset) your ram''s fatigue counter by stopping at barrels of apples which can be found on the ram riding paths.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=11412][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=11122][/icon][/b] - Awards 10 [item=37829]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=24497][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23558][/icon]\nThis quest is a little challenging, you are once again granted a temporary ram mount that lasts 4 minutes and you must use the [item=33306] and your new-found skill of ram riding to receive and deliver kegs of brew between the goblins. You must travel down the path, minding your speed and fatigue, and you will be thrown a [item=33797] by either [icon name=side_horde][npc=24527][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=24364][/icon]. Simply return the keg to the questgiver three times to successfully complete the quest. I highly recommend moving as quickly as possible and stopping momentarily at every barrel of apples to insure you do not reach 100 fatigue. After completing this quest, the questgiver will allow you to help him out one more time per day.[pad][/li]\n\n[li]Every 18 Hours: [b]''Do you still need some help moving kegs from the crash site... ?''[/b] - Awards 2 [item=37829] per turn-in\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=24497][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23558][/icon]\nThis isn''t exactly a quest, per se, but is a very good option for accumulating more [item=37829]. This "quest" is available after successfully completing [b]There and Back Again[/b]. Simply speak to the NPC again and offer to help him out again. The questgiver will give you another ram with which you must retrieve and return more kegs, awarding 2 [item=37829] per loop. You can do this as many times as possible until your ram mount expires (4 minutes). You can only offer to help him once [b]every 18 hours[/b], and only after completing the initial quest.[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3][icon name=inv_cask_03]Daily Quests[/icon][/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b]Bark for ________![/b] - Awards 15 [item=37829]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=24498][/icon] / [icon name=side_horde][npc=24499][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23628][/icon] / [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23627][/icon]\nThis quest can be started at either of the rivaling breweries, and may only be completed for one brewery per day. Horde players can choose to either [icon name=side_horde][quest=11407][/icon] or [icon name=side_horde][quest=11408][/icon] and Alliance choose between [icon name=side_alliance][quest=11293][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][quest=11294][/icon]. It does not matter which brewery you choose to bark for, and you can even choose a different one each day (though don''t tell the other guys)! For this quest you are yet again given the ram and [item=33306] and this time must run throughout your capital city, visiting different designated checkpoints to preach the great word of brew within a 4 minute time limit. This quest can be rather challenging, as there are no apple barrels to renew your ram''s fatigue so it''s best to keep a steady (albeit annoyingly slow) pace as you travel throughout your city. Once you reach the fourth location, provided your time, many players opt to cancel the ram buff and simply mount on a regular epic mount to go return the quest.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=12192][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=12020][/icon][/b] - Awards 10 [item=37829]\n[b]Start:[/b] [url=?object=189989]Dark Iron Mole Machine Wreckage[/url]\n[b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=27216][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=27215][/icon]\nThis quest can only be picked up after a Dark Iron invasion on the Brewfest camp (every 30 minutes). Simply pick up beer from the nearby kegs and attempt to hit the invading Dark Iron Dwarves until they depart. Once the dwarves have been defeated and retreat, a piece of [url=?object=189989]Dark Iron Mole Machine Wreckage[/url] will remain on the ground that anyone can loot to obtain this quest. You can then turn the quest in nearby and receive your tokens.[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n\n\n[h2]Brewfest Spoils![/h2]\nQuests completed during Brewfest will award [item=37829] which can be redeemed for items by speaking to either [icon name=side_horde][npc=24495][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23710][/icon], located at the main Brewfest camps outside of [zone=1637] and [zone=1537], respectively. These items can also be purchased during Brewfest from the Brew of the Month club vendors found inside the two cities, [icon name=side_horde][npc=27489][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=27478][/icon]. Here is a full list of the items they have for sale!\n[pad]\n[table class=grid width=40%]\n[tr][td][b]Item[/b][/td][td align=center width=25%][b]Cost[/b][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=33968][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,50][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=33967][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,50][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=33864][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,50][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=33969][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,50][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=33863][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,200][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=33966][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,100][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=33862][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,200][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=33868][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,100][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]"Brew of the Month" Club Membership Form[br] ([url=?item=37571]Alliance[/url] or [url=?item=37599]Horde[/url])[/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,200][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=34008] or [item=33047][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,100][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][div float=right margin=0px][small][i]Limited duration[/i][/small][/div][item=39477] or [item=39476][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,5][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][div float=right margin=0px][small][i]Limited duration[/i][/small][/div][item=37750][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,2][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=37816][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,20][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=33927][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,100][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td][item=46707][/td][td align=center][money=0 items=37829,100][/td][/tr]\n[/table]\n\nThe Brewfest gear is perfect for dressing up the occasion and prancing about looking pretty fancy. The [item=46707] is a cute little pink elekk non-combat pet that can only be seen by party/raid members or incredibly drunk individuals. The "Brew of the Month" Club Membership ([url=?item=37571]Alliance[/url] / [url=?item=37599]Horde[/url]) starts a quest that is completed in your respective faction''s major city and enrolls your character in the Brew of the Month Club where you will receive a new brew in the mail every month, delicious drinks with quite interesting side-effects! The [item=34008], when equipped, will change everyone you see into a female orc (Horde) or male gnome (Alliance) - dead sexy, right? The [item=37750] are temporary items that will expire and change your mount into either a Brewfest Kodo (Horde) or Brewfest Ram (Alliance), the [item=39477] (available to Horde) will change your mount into a Brewfest Ram and the [item=39476] (available to Alliance) will change your mount into a Brewfest Kodo. Finally, the [item=33927] places a keg on the ground that anyone can use to retrieve a [item=33929].\n\nIn addition the Brewfest items for sale by the token vendors, there are also a variety of food/drink sellers found in the camps, selling wine, cheese, sausage, bread and (of course) booze to the festival patrons.\n\nPlayers at level 80 will be interested in the event boss [npc=23872], who can be found in [zone=1584]. Players can try for their chance at a [item=33977] or [item=37828] (or maybe even both)!\n\n\n[h2]Coren Direbrew, The Grim Guzzler and the Dark Iron Dwarves![/h2]\nBrewfest veterans surely remember the exploits of one [npc=23872], found deep inside [zone=1584]'' Grim Guzzler bar. Coren Direbrew is now a [b]level 80+ boss[/b] and drops trinkets which are equivalent to the [item=40752] trinkets, along with upgraded versions of his previous loot.\n\nYou can queue up for Coren Direbrew using the Dungeon Finder tool as low as [b]level 78[/b]. Upon killing Coren Direbrew for the first time, he will drop a quest item, [item=38281], which starts the quest [quest=12492] ([url=/?quest=12491]Alliance version[/url]). Turning in this quest will award 40 [item=37829].\n\nOn your first kill of each day, you will also be awarded a [item=54535], which contains 2 [item=49426] and has a chance to contain awesome items! You will be awarded [money=198600] at level 80, as well. You can get only one [item=54535] per day, so there is no longer a point to farming the boss if you don''t need any of the trinkets he drops!\n\n[h3]Gimme the loot![/h3]\nCoren Direbrew himself drops epic quality (item level 200) trinkets which are the equivalent of Wrath of the Lich King''s first tier [item=40752] trinkets. These trinkets are unique from the Emblem trinkets and can be used one after another after a normal trinket use delay of 20 seconds. Once again, these items cannot be disenchanted - so no free crystals!\n[ul]\n[li][item=49080] ([item=40683])[/li]\n[li][item=49076] ([item=40682])[/li]\n[li][item=49074] ([item=40684])[/li]\n[li][item=49078] ([item=40685])[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nCoren also has a chance to drop +170 stamina trinkets that summon the Brewmaiden who will heal your party or the Black Brewmaiden who will chuck beer at your enemies! In addition, both maidens can be /wave''d at to receive free brew!\n[ul]\n[li][item=49118][/li]\n[li][item=49116][/li]\n[/ul]\n\nThe first time you defeat Coren Direbrew each day, you will be awarded a [color=q3]Keg-Shaped Treasure Chest[/color]. The treasure chest contains 2 [item=49426] and has a chance of containing Coren Direbrew''s non-trinket drops (y''know, the good stuff). You can get more than one of these items per chest!\n[ul]\n[li][item=37828][/li]\n[li][item=33977][/li]\n[li][item=49120][/li]\n[li][item=48663][/li]\n[li][item=37863][/li]\n[/ul]\n\nRemember you will only be rewarded one chest per day, so that''s only one chance at all of the more rare drops - so no more mindlessly farming Coren into the late hours just to try and get the mounts! I know I won''t miss it.\n\n[h2]Brewfest Achievements[/h2]\n\nBrewfest is more than just standing around dressing funny and drinking grog! In the midst of the unruly behavior and excessive consumption of alcoholic beverages, there''s a new title to be earned - [i]Brewmaster[/i]! For many players, completing the Brewfest achievements will finally earn them [achievement=2145], so we can expect to start seeing some beautiful [spell=60024]s flying around!\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1683][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1684][/icon][/b]\nComplete all of the Brewfest achievements [i]except[/i] Brew of the Year, [achievement=1260], Strange Brew and [achievement=293] and you will be awarded the player title [b]''Brewmaster''[/b]. That''s right, with the addition of [achievement=2796] players are no longer required to spend an entire year waiting to complete the [achievement=1183] achievement as a meta for [achievement=2145].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=2796][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must purchase a [item=37571] for 200 [item=37829] from either [icon name=side_horde][npc=24495][/icon], [icon name=side_horde][npc=27489][/icon], [icon name=side_alliance][npc=23710][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=27478][/icon] at the main Brewfest camps or inside [zone=1637] or [zone=1537]. This will entitle you to receive a special brew every month, for members only! You will be able to purchase more of a specific month''s brew from a Brew Vendor located inside [url=/?zone=1637]Orgrimmar[/url] or [zone=1537].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1183][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must drink one of each of the 12 beers featured in the Brew of the Month club. You will recieve a new brew at the beginning of every month, and will only be able to purchase that brew for the duration of that month so be sure you don''t miss one! This achievement will take a full year to get, but thankfully it is no longer required for the [achievement=1683] achievement.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=295][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must travel to the Bar of [zone=1584] and defeat the Dark Iron dwarf [npc=23872].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=293][/b]\nFor this achievement, you must purchase and wear three pieces of [url=?items=4&filter=na=Brewfest#0+7+1]Brewfest clothing[/url] (a hat, boots, and chest), get completely smashed from the alcohol of your choice and /dance in [url=/?zone=4395]Dalaran[/url].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1936][/b]\nFor this acheivement, you must complete the quest [icon name=side_horde][quest=11431][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][quest=11117][/icon] and obtain the [item=32233]. Enjoy your cute/creepy pet![pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1186][/b]\nDefend the Brewfest camp from a Dark Iron attack and complete the quest, [quest=12192] ([quest=12020]). The Dark Iron attacks happen roughly every half hour at either of the main Brewfest camps, located outside of [zone=1637] or [zone=1537]. Once you have ''defeated'' the Dark Iron attack, simply loot the [url=/?object=189989]Dark Iron Mole Machine Wreckage[/url] which will start the required quest, which can be turned in nearby.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1260][/b]\nThis achievement is just a Brewfest version of [achievement=964], so any strategies/locations specified for that will apply. Just remember to get really, really intoxicated beforehand (ie. "completely smashed") and try to survive the fall![pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=303][/b]\nFor this achievement, you can now either own a Brewfest mount (either dropped by [npc=23872] or obtained via tokens in 2007) or simply change one of your existing mounts into one by using [item=37750], which can be purchased from Brewfest vendors for a mere 2 [item=37829]. You can also use the other types of Hops, though these will cost more [item=37829]. [pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1203][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1184][/icon][/b]\nFor this achievement, simply sample one of each of the beers available from your faction''s Brewfest vendors. These beers can be purchased at the Brewfest camps found outside of any major city.\n[icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon] players will purchase brews from [npc=23533], [npc=24501] and [npc=23511].\n[icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon] players will purchase brews from [npc=23510], [npc=23482] and [npc=23511].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1185][/b]\nFor this achievement, simply sample one of each of the foods available from the Brewfest vendors.\n[icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon] players will purchase food from [npc=23605], [npc=23604] and [npc=23603].\n[icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon] players will purchase food from [npc=23481], [npc=23521] and [npc=23522].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=3496][/b]\nThis achievement is a Feat of Strength, so it will not award Achievement Points (oh no :P) or count towards any other achievement progress. This achievement is awarded for obtaining either of the epic Brewfest mounts dropped by [npc=23872] in [url=/?zone=1584]Blackrock Depths[/url] - either the Swift Brewfest Kodo or [item=33977]. Good luck![pad][/li]\n[/ul]'),
    (300,7,0,'hallows-end','[menu tab=6 path=6,3,hallows-end]\n\nIt''s that time again folks—time to dress up in a ridiculous costume, and go score some treats!  It''s [url=?achievements=158]Hallow''s End[/url]!\n\n[div class="minibox" style="text-align:left; clear:right"][toc][/div]\n\n[h2]Treats and Goodies![/h2]\n\nThere are three major sources of fun, seasonal items that can be acquired during the Hallow''s End festival: \n[item=20393], [item=34077], and the [url=?npc=23682]Headless Horseman[/url].\n\n[item=20393] can be obtained via [url=?spell=24751]Trick or Treating[/url] with the innkeeper of a friendly inn. If the innkeeper decides to give you a treat, he will award you a [item=20393], which has a chance to contain a Flimsy Mask, Hallowed Wand, or even [item=33154] or [item=33292]! However, the innkeeper may instead opt to play a trick on you, typically shapeshifting you into a bat, cat, ghost or pirate. Once you have trick or treated on a character, you will gain the [spell=24755] debuff which will prevent you from Trick or Treating for [b]one hour[/b].\n\nA [item=34077] can be obtained after protecting a low level Alliance (Goldshire, Kharanos, or Azure Watch) or Horde (Razor Hill, Falconwing Square, or Brill) village from the [url=?npc=23543]Shade of the Horseman[/url] (see the Quests section below). The matrons located in these villages will ask for your aid in putting out fires in local buildings. When the [url=?npc=23543]Shade of the Horseman[/url] has been defeated, a large Jack-o-Lantern will appear on the ground that gives the quest [b][quest=12155] ([url=?quest=12133]Alliance[/url])[/b] which can be turned in at the nearby Matron. The Matron will reward you with a sum of gold and a [item=34077], which can contain candy, masks, or even riding brooms!\n\nThe [url=?npc=23682]Headless Horseman[/url] is a level 80 boss that players can queue up for using the Dungeon Finder tool. The boss will then spawn in the Graveyard of [url=?zone=796]Scarlet Monastery[/url]. This encounter can be completed easily by a decently-geared 5-man of level 80 players. For more information check out the [url=#headlesshorseman]section below[/url]!\n\n[h2]Candy Buckets[/h2]\nSeasonal, pumpkin-shaped Candy Buckets are located inside every inn, near the Innkeeper. Each bucket offers a one-time quest that can be completed and rewards a small sum of gold and a [item=37586], which contains a small assortment of seasonal snacks. These snacks include [item=37582], [item=37583], [item=37585], and [item=37584]. Visiting all friendly inn buckets on continent will reward an achievement.\n\n[h3]Locations[/h3]\n\nCheck out the related achievements below for a list of all buckets.\n\n[ul]\n[li]Eastern Kingdoms: [url=/?achievement=966]Alliance[/url] / [url=/?achievement=967]Horde[/url][/li]\n[li]Kalimdor: [url=/?achievement=963]Alliance[/url] / [url=/?achievement=965]Horde[/url][/li]\n[li]Outland: [url=/?achievement=969]Alliance[/url] / [url=/?achievement=968]Horde[/url][/li]\n[li]Northrend: Buckets are located in inns, unfortunately there is no achievement for these treat buckets.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h2]Quests[/h2]\n\n[h3][icon name=side_horde]Horde Quests[/icon][/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11357][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=19175][/icon]\n[b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=23973][/icon]\nThis quest is just a breadcrumb quest intended to lead you to a Masked Orphan Matron located at one of the low level Horde villages, either Razor Hill, Falconwing Square, or Brill. This quest does not need to be completed in order to take the Matron''s other quests.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=11361][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=23973][/icon]\nThis quest can be started in either Razor Hill ([zone=14]), Falconwing Square ([zone=3430]) or Brill ([zone=85]), but only completed once, at a single location. The Matron will direct you to a nearby water barrel from which you can collect [item=32971] that can be thrown at flames. There will be test fires that you can put out by simply ''using'' the bucket and aiming at the fires. When you have successfully hit 5 fires, return to the Matron for your reward.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=12139][/b] / [b][quest=11219][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=23973][/icon]\nThe availability of this daily quest is situational - if the village you are in is not yet under attack by the [npc=23543], the Matron will offer [quest=12139] which you cannot complete until the village is under attack. However, if you first speak to the Matron while the village is currently under attack, she will instead offer [quest=11219], which is the same quest basically with just a different title. Simply aid in extinguishing all of the fires the Shade has started, then speak to the Matron. This is a daily quest.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=8312][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=15309][/icon]\nThis quest asks that you collect a variety of holiday treats from the innkeepers of major faction cities. However, they won''t be giving the goodies away without a price! You must perform a different emote to each innkeeper before being rewarded the quest item.\n[ul]\n[li][item=20493] is rewarded from [quest=8359][/li]\n[li][item=20495] is rewarded from [quest=8358][/li]\n[li][item=20491] is rewarded from [quest=8354][/li]\n[li][item=20497] is rewarded from [quest=8360][/li]\n[/ul][pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=1657][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=15197][/icon]\nThis quest requires "sneaking" into Southshore and throwing stink bombs into the middle of town. Not an incredibly difficult quest, though can be quite challenging to lower leveled players. Best to group with higher levels and watch out for guards! This quest is a requirement for the achievement [achievement=1041].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=8322][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=15197][/icon]\n[b]End:[/b] [object=180570]\nFor this quest you must sneak into the Southshore Inn and place the [item=20605] inside the kegs, which are located near the second floor stairs. Upon doing so, the quest will complete and a new quest will become available. This quest is a requirement for the achievement [achievement=1041].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=8409][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [object=180570]\n[b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=15197][/icon]\nUpon sucessfully completing [b][quest=8322][/b], simply return to [npc=15197] to declare your victory and celebrate with [item=20557]! This quest is a requirement for the achievement [achievement=1041].[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance Quests[/icon][/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=11356][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [icon name=side_alliance][npc=18927][/icon]\n[b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_alliance][npc=24519][/icon]\nThis quest is just a breadcrumb quest intended to lead you to a Costumed Orphan Matron located at one of the low level Alliance villages, either Goldshire, Kharanos, or Azure Watch. This quest does not need to be completed in order to take the Matron''s other quests.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=11360][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_alliance][npc=24519][/icon]\nThis quest can be started in either Goldshire ([zone=12]), Kharanos ([zone=1]), or Azure Watch ([zone=3524]), but only completed once, at a single location. The Matron will direct you to a nearby water barrel from which you can collect [item=32971] that can be thrown at flames. There will be test fires that you can put out by simply ''using'' the bucket and aiming at the fires. When you have successfully hit 5 fires, return to the Matron for your reward.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=12135][/b] / [b][quest=11131][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_alliance][npc=24519][/icon]\nThe availability of this daily quest is situational - if the village you are in is not yet under attack by the [npc=23543], the Matron will offer [quest=12135] which you cannot complete until the village is under attack. However, if you first speak to the Matron while the village is currently under attack, she will instead offer [quest=11131], which is the same quest basically with just a different title. Simply aid in extinguishing all of the fires the Shade has started, then speak to the Matron. This is a daily quest.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=8311][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_alliance][npc=15310][/icon]\nThis quest asks that you collect a variety of holiday treats from the innkeepers of major faction cities. However, they won''t be giving the goodies away without a price! You must perform a different emote to each innkeeper before being rewarded the quest item.\n[ul]\n[li][item=20492] is rewarded from [quest=8356][/li]\n[li][item=20494] is rewarded from [quest=8355][/li]\n[li][item=20490] is rewarded from [quest=8353][/li]\n[li][item=20496] is rewarded from [quest=8357][/li]\n[/ul][pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=8373][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_alliance][npc=15199][/icon]\nThis quest can only be completed after a Horde player has done [b][quest=1657][/b]. Use the [item=20604] to clean up a Stink Bomb that has been dropped in the middle of Southshore (it looks like a large, red cloud). This quest is a requirement for the achievement [achievement=1040].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=1658][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_alliance][npc=15199][/icon]\nFor this quest, Alliance players must travel to Tirisfal Glades and discover the Forsaken''s Wickerman Festival. Fairly easy quest provided there is no Horde opposition, simply mount up and head just Southwest of the entrance to Undercity. Try to avoid the abomination and guards![pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[anchor=headlesshorseman][h2]The Headless Horseman[/h2]\n\nThe Headless Horseman is a level 80+ 5-man boss located in the Graveyard of [zone=796]. This boss will only spawn for level 78+ players who have queued for the encounter via the Dungeon Finder tool. The boss drops epic-quality equipment, and additional fun loot can be obtained from a special [color=q3]Loot-Filled Pumpkin[/color] awarded once per day for killing him.\n\nRemember, you can queue up for the boss as many times as you like, but you will only have access to his regular drops - the [color=q3]Loot-Filled Pumpkin[/color] and a monetary reward of [money=198600] will only be awarded once per day - which means only one chance per character per day to get [item=37012]!\n\n[h3]Phat Lewts![/h3]\n[b]Boss Loot[/b]\n[ul]\n[li]Ring: [item=49121] [color=q0](physical DPS)[/color][/li]\n[li]Ring: [item=49123] [color=q0](caster DPS)[/color][/li]\n[li]Ring: [item=49124] [color=q0](healing)[/color][/li]\n[/ul]\n[b]Daily [color=q3]Loot-Filled Pumpkin[/color] Loot[/b]\n[ul]\n[li]Sword: [item=49128][/li]\n[li]Helm: [item=49126][/li]\n[li]Mount: [item=37012][/li]\n[li]Temporary Mount: [item=33176][/li]\n[li]Small Pet: [item=33154][/li]\n[li]Pumpkin Helm: [item=33292][/li]\n[/ul]\nThe Loot-Filled Pumpkin can also contain a randomly selected flimsy mask (if no "special" loot is awarded). It is possible to get multiple special items from the bag at the same time! \n\n[h2]Achievements[/h2]\n\nThere are a total of 22 achievements that can be obtained during Hallow''s End! While running about sporting hauntingly fun Hallow''s End masks and gorging on candy, find time to earn some achievements and be awarded a cool player title - [i]the Hallowed[/i]! Completeing the achievements required for [achievement=1657] will, of course, count towards [achievement=2145] and towards earning the beautiful [item=44177]!\n\n[ul]\n[li][b][achievement=1657][/b]\n[small][b]Complete the Hallow''s End achievements listed below.[/b][/small]\nThis achievement requires the completion of 11 particular achievements and awards the player title, "[b]The Hallowed[/b]." The 11 achievements that must be completed are: [b][achievement=972], [achievement=288], [achievement=255], [achievement=289], [achievement=981], [achievement=1040], [achievement=1261], [achievement=291], [achievement=283], [achievement=292][/b], and [b][achievement=971] ([url=?achievement=970]Alliance[/url])[/b].\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=284][/b]\n[small][b]Collect the 20 unique Flimsy Masks listed below.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must obtain [i]every single[/i] [url=?search=Flimsy+Mask]Flimsy Mask[/url]. This will be a very difficult achievement to complete and thankfully is not a requirement of [achievement=1656]. The Flimsy Masks are bind on pickup, so in order to try and obtain all of the masks you should Trick or Treat as often as possible. Since there are a total of 20 Flimsy Masks required for this achievement, and the masks are a random drop, you may not be able to complete this one at least until next Hallow''s End. May luck be on your side!\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=255][/b]\n[small][b]Kill the Headless Horseman.[/b][/small]\nThis achievement is pretty straight-forward - simply kill the [npc=23682] in [zone=796]. Please note that you must be of level 78 or higher to summon him, though it may be possible to achieve this at a lower level with a party of higher level characters.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=291][/b]\n[small][b]Use Weighted Jack-o''-Lanterns to put pumpkin heads on each of the races listed below.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must use a [item=34068] on at least one of every Alliance and Horde race. The Jack-o''-Lanterns can be looted from the [npc=23682] or received in the [item=34077] available after defeating the Headless Horseman in one of the low level villages as detailed above in the Quests section. They are also rewarded from the related daily quest.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1261][/b]\n[small][b]Earn 50 honorable kills while under the influence of the G.N.E.R.D. buff. It''s a slap in the face![/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, earn 50 honorable kills (total) while buffed by the Hallow''s End candy [item=37583]. The candy is a just small dodge buff so the achievement is really just a silly pun.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=288][/b]\n[small][b]Eat so many Tricky Treats that you get an upset tummy.[/b][/small]\n[item=33226] "drop" from the [npc=23682] and offer a small speed boost in addition to eventually giving you an [spell=42966]. \n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][icon name=side_alliance][b][achievement=1040][/b][/icon]\n[small][b]Ruin Hallow''s End for the Horde by completing [npc=15199]''s quests which involve crashing the wickerman festival and cleaning up the stinkbombs from Southshore.[/b][/small]\nComplete the seasonal quests [b][quest=1658][/b] and [b][quest=8373][/b].\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][icon name=side_horde][b][achievement=1041][/b][/icon]\n[small][b]Ruin Hallow''s End for the Alliance by completing [npc=15197]''s quests which involve going to Southshore, ruining the kegs with rotten eggs and tossing stinkbombs into the town.[/b][/small]\nComplete the seasonal quests [b][quest=1657][/b] and [b][quest=8322][/b] / [b][quest=8409][/b],\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=292][/b]\n[small][b]Obtain a Sinister Squashling pet and Hallowed Helm.[/b][/small]\nOne of the most difficult achievements to obtain due to sheer luck factor, for this one you must obtain both the [url=?item=33154]Sinister Squashling[/url] vanity pet and the [url=?item=33292]Hallowed Helm[/url] off the [url=?npc=23682]Headless Horseman[/url].\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=981][/b]\n[small][b]Show off your sparkling smile by using a Tooth Pick.[/b][/small]\nUse a [item=37604], which has a chance to drop from the [item=20393] obtained via Trick or Treating.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=979][/b]\n[small][b]Obtain a Flimsy Mask during Hallow''s End.[/b][/small]\nObtain a [url=?search=Flimsy+Mask]Flimsy Mask[/url], which has a chance to drop from the [item=20393] obtained via Trick or Treating.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=283][/b]\n[small][b]Get transformed by the Hallowed Wands listed below.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must be transformed by each specific costume [url=?search=Hallowed+Wand]Hallowed Wand[/url]. The ''Random'' wand will not count towards the achievement. It is best to trade costumes with other players who have the ones you want!\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=289][/b]\n[small][b]Complete one of the quests to save a village from the Headless Horseman.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must complete one of the quests to save a burning village from the [npc=23543] - either [b][quest=12135][/b] or [b][quest=11131][/b].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=972][/b]\n[small][b]Receive a handful of a candy from one of the Candy Buckets located in an inn.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, all you have to do is visit a single Candy Bucket located within any friendly inn and loot a handful of candy\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=971][/icon] / [icon name=side_alliance][achievement=970][/icon][/b]\n[small][b]Complete the Kalimdor, Eastern Kingdoms and Outland Tricks and Treats achievements.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must complete each of the three following achievements, essentially having visited every possible Candy Bucket.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=967][/icon] / [icon name=side_alliance][achievement=966][/icon][/b]\n[small][b]Visit the Candy Buckets in Eastern Kingdoms.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must visit every single Candy Bucket in the Eastern Kingdoms. The candy buckets are located in friendly faction inns. For a full list of bucket locations, visit the achievement page for your respective faction.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=965][/icon] / [icon name=side_alliance][achievement=963][/icon][/b]\n[small][b]Visit the Candy Buckets in Kalimdor.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must visit every single Candy Bucket in Kalimdor. The candy buckets are located in friendly faction inns. For a full list of bucket locations, visit the achievement page for your respective faction.\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=968][/icon] / [icon name=side_alliance][achievement=969][/icon][/b]\n[small][b]Visit the Candy Buckets in Outland.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must visit every single Candy Bucket in Outland. The candy buckets are located in friendly faction inns. For a full list of bucket locations, visit the achievement page for your respective faction.\n[pad][/li]\n[/ul]'),
    (300,8,0,'pilgrims-bounty','[menu tab=6 path=6,3,pilgrims-bounty]\n\n[i]It''s time to reflect on your journeys and good fortune, share plentiful food, and stories with friends. You can partake in wonderful [url=event=26]Pilgrim''s Bounty[/url] feasts near major towns by sitting at a [url=#bountiful-tables]Bountiful Table[/url] and enjoying the foods you find there.[/i]\n\n[div class="minibox" style="text-align:left; clear:right"][toc][/div]\n\n[h2]Bountiful Tables[/h2]\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/pilgrims-bounty/table.jpg float=right border=0]The main Pilgrim''s Bounty festivities take place at Bountiful Tables which can be found located throughout many zones in Kalimdor and Eastern Kingdoms. Various seasonal vendors and questgivers surround the major cities'' tables, offering special cooking ingredients and the related daily quests.\n\nBountiful Tables can be found at the following locations:\n\n[h3][icon name=side_horde]Horde Locations[/icon][/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b]Major cities:[/b] Orgrimmar, Silvermoon City, Thunder Bluff, Undercity[/li]\n[li][b]Minor towns:[/b] Bloodhoof Village, Brill, Falconwing Square, Hammerfall, Razor Hill,  Revantusk Village, Sepulcher, Shadowprey Village, Stonard, Tarren Mill, Tranquillien[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance Locations[/icon][/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b]Major cities:[/b] Darnassus, Exodar, Ironforge, Stormwind City[/li]\n[li][b]Minor towns:[/b] Azure Watch, Chillwind Camp, Dolanaar, Goldshire, Kharanos, Southshore, Wildhammer Keep[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3][icon name=side_both]Neutral Locations[/icon][/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b]Minor towns:[/b] Light''s Hope Chapel, Ruins of Thaurissan[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nAt any of these locations you will find that Bountiful Tables have been set up and loaded with delicious food! The Tables located in major cities will be surrounded by vendors, cooking trainers, and questgivers while the ones located in minor towns will have only a Bountiful Table Hostess to greet you. You can sit and eat at any Bountiful Table - even those located in the opposing faction''s city/town. In fact, there''s even an [url=/?achievement=3580]achieve[/url][url=/?achievement=3581]ment[/url] for doing just that!\n\nA Bountiful Table features five different chairs, one for each different food that is available in that spot. Each chair is labeled for the associated food, and you will be able to eat/pass as much of it as possible for as long as you are seated. Each Bountiful Table will feature [b][npc=34823][/b], [b][npc=34822][/b], [b][npc=34824][/b], [b][npc=34819][/b], and (of course) [b][npc=34812][/b]. Unlike normal chairs, the Bountiful Table''s chairs function similar to vehicles and feature their own unique abilities that will replace your main action bar upon being seated.\n\nPlayers will be given options to eat or pass the delicious foods provided at their seat. These abilities are necessary not only for eating to obtain the respective food''s buff (you must eat five helpings of a single food to gain its buff), but also to pass the foods required for [achievement=3558] and to accidentally "throw" the food required for [achievement=3579].\n\nIf you eat five helpings of each of the available foods at a Bountiful Table, you will gain the [spell=61849 buff=true] buff which grants a 10% increase in reputation gain for an hour, and can be regained simply by visiting a table and sampling all five foods again. If seated players pass food to each other, obtaining this buff shouldn''t take long at all - so don''t forget to share!\n\n[h2]Seasonal Items[/h2]\n\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/pilgrims-bounty/cornucopia.jpg float=right border=0]The ingredients required for cooking the various Pilgrim''s Bounty recipes are available only from special seasonal vendors or from mobs that will not spawn outside of the season.\n\nWhile these reagents do not seem to have any duration (or specific holiday requirement), I don''t think anyone will really bother stockpiling any of it (except, of course, for any druid''s bear necessity to carry around some [item=44853]). The recipes will at least count towards the various recipe-learning achievements (such as [achievement=1799]).\n\nThe following items can be purchased from seasonal vendors and used to cook the new recipes, and some can only be purchased in a specific zone (see item tooltips):\n[ul]\n[li][item=44835] - 5 for [money=10][/li]\n[li][item=44853] - 5 for [money=25][/li]\n[li][item=46797] or [item=44855] - 5 for [money=25][/li]\n[li][item=46793] or [item=44854] - 5 for [money=25][/li]\n[li][item=46796] or [item=46784] - 5 for [money=25][/li]\n[/ul]\n\nIn addition to those ingredients, Pilgrim''s Bounty Vendors will also sell:\n[ul]\n[li][item=46809] or [item=46810] - [money=1000][/li]\n[li][item=159] - 5 for [money=25][/li]\n[li][item=2678] - 5 for [money=10][/li]\n[li][item=30817] - 5 for [money=25][/li]\n[li][item=46888] - [money=2000][/li]\n[/ul]\n\nUpon completing the quest chain ending with [quest=14047] ([url=/?quest=14035]Alliance version[/url]), you will receive a [item=44844]. This fun little item can be used to call a [npc=32820] to your side (which can then be killed for [item=44834]). This is not to be confused with the non-combat pet you can obtain by completing all of the Pilgrim''s Bounty achievements, and will expire when the event has ended.\n\nThere are also few new seasonal items that are available as rewards from the various Cooking daily quests. You will have your choice of any one reward for completing a daily quest, so you will be able to collect all of the different rewards after completing [b]five[/b] daily quests. You will then need to complete [b]eight[/b] more daily quests in order to get enough [item=44812] to transform each different race of rogue for [achievement=3559].\n\nYou will need to complete at least ten daily quests in order to obtain enough items to complete various achievements (a Pilgrim Hat, your choice of chestpiece, and the 8 [item=44812]). The following items are awarded from the Pilgrim''s Bounty daily quests:\n\n[ul]\n[li][item=46723][/li]\n[li][item=46800][/li]\n[li][item=44785][/li]\n[li][item=46824][/li]\n[li][item=44788][/li]\n[li][item=44812][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h2]Seasonal Recipes[/h2]\n\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/pilgrims-bounty/corn.jpg float=right border=0]With the main focus of the Pilgrim''s Bounty event being [i]food[/i] (oh, and y''know, giving thanks and sharing and all that), you had better believe there''s new [spell=51296] recipes! Seasonal recipes have been added and players can purchase a [item=46810] ([url=?item=46809]Alliance version[/url]) containing all five of their faction''s recipes for a mere [money=100] from any Pilgrim''s Bounty Vendor!\n\nIt is worth mentioning that learning and cooking these seasonal recipes provides one of the easiest and fastest methods of leveling Cooking from [i]at least[/i] 1 - 300 skill using only seasonal, vendor-purchased ingredients, so if your character has no Cooking skill now is the perfect time to start!\n\n[h3][icon name=side_horde]Horde Recipes[/icon][/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b][spell=66038][/b] - Taught by [item=46803]\nThis recipe requires [b]1[/b] [spell=2550] and the following ingredients: [item=30816], [item=44835].\nThis food will restore 4% of your health/mana every second for 30 seconds, and grants an one hour [b]Hit Rating[/b] and [b]Stamina[/b] buff.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][spell=66036][/b] - Taught by [item=46804]\nThis recipe requires [b]100[/b] [spell=3102] and the following ingredients: [item=46796], [item=44853].\nThis food will restore 4% of your health/mana every second for 30 seconds, and grants an one hour [b]Spirit[/b] and [b]Stamina[/b] buff.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][spell=66035][/b] - Taught by [item=46805]\nThis recipe requires [b]160[/b] [spell=3413] and the following ingredients: [item=46793], [item=44853].\nThis food will restore 4% of your health/mana every second for 30 seconds, and grants an one hour [b]Spell Power[/b] and [b]Stamina[/b] buff.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][spell=66034][/b] - Taught by [item=46806]\nThis recipe requires [b]220[/b] [spell=3413] and the following ingredients: [item=46797], [item=44853], [item=44835]. \nThis food will restore 4% of your health/mana every second for 30 seconds, and grants an one hour [b]Haste Rating[/b] and [b]Stamina[/b] buff.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][spell=66037][/b] - Taught by [item=46807]\nThis recipe requires [b]280[/b] [spell=18260] and the following ingredients: [item=44834], [item=44853] (2),  [item=44835].\nThis food will restore 4% of your health/mana every second for 30 seconds, and grants an one hour [b]Attack Power[/b] and [b]Stamina[/b] buff.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance Recipes[/icon][/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b][spell=62050][/b] - Taught by [item=44860]\nThis recipe requires [b]1[/b] [spell=2550] and the following ingredients: [item=30816], [item=44835].\nThis food will restore 4% of your health/mana every second for 30 seconds, and grants an one hour [b]Hit Rating[/b] and [b]Stamina[/b] buff.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][spell=62044][/b] - Taught by [item=44862]\nThis recipe requires [b]100[/b] [spell=3102] and the following ingredients: [item=46784], [item=44853].\nThis food will restore 4% of your health/mana every second for 30 seconds, and grants an one hour [b]Spirit[/b] and [b]Stamina[/b] buff.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][spell=62049][/b] - Taught by [item=44858]\nThis recipe requires [b]160[/b] [spell=3413] and the following ingredients: [item=44854], [item=44853].\nThis food will restore 4% of your health/mana every second for 30 seconds, and grants an one hour [b]Spell Power[/b] and [b]Stamina[/b] buff.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][spell=62051][/b] - Taught by [item=44859]\nThis recipe requires [b]220[/b] [spell=3413] and the following ingredients: [item=44855], [item=44853], [item=44835]. \nThis food will restore 4% of your health/mana every second for 30 seconds, and grants an one hour [b]Haste Rating[/b] and [b]Stamina[/b] buff.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][spell=62045][/b] - Taught by [item=44861]\nThis recipe requires [b]280[/b] [spell=18260] and the following ingredients: [item=44834], [item=44853] (2),  [item=44835].\nThis food will restore 4% of your health/mana every second for 30 seconds, and grants an one hour [b]Attack Power[/b] and [b]Stamina[/b] buff.[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\nNew Pilgrim''s Bounty Vendors have been added that sell most of the reagents required for cooking these recipes. Certain specific ingredients can only be purchased at their respective cities, for example [item=46797] can only be purchased in [zone=215], near [zone=1638]. The only item you will have to go out and farm for is the [item=44834], which will require traveling out to either [zone=85] or [zone=12] and killing [npc=32820]. Thankfully, the [item=44834] is a 100% drop and these delicious critters don''t put up much of a fight.\n\nIt is also worth mentioning that one of the recipes ([spell=66038] / [spell=62050]) requires [item=30816], which is created by another Cooking recipe unrelated to the holiday. This recipe, [spell=37836], can be trained from pretty much any Cooking Trainer and requires only 1 point in [spell=2550] skill, making it a great leveling recipe as well.\n\n[h2]Quests[/h2]\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/pilgrims-bounty/hat.jpg float=right border=0]Pilgrim''s Bounty features a number of new cooking-oriented quests, most of which have daily quest versions as well.\n\nYou will need at [i]least[/i] [b]330 [spell=33359] skill[/b] in order to be able to cook all of the new seasonal recipes, though the recipes have varying skill levels so if you are not interested in completing everything there will definitely be a recipe you will be able to cook for at least one daily quest, provided you have any Cooking skill at all.\n\nThe recipes required for these quests can be learned from a Pilgrim''s Bounty Cooking Trainer located near the major cities'' Bountiful Tables.\n\n[h3][icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon] Quests[/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=14036][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] Commoners located inside major cities.\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34677]\nThis is simply a breadcrumb quest that leads you to out to the Pilgrim''s Bounty celebrations in [zone=1497]''s courtyard, the Ruins of Lordaeron, and is not necessary to be completed in order to obtain the other quests. Simply head out that way and talk to Miles Standish to complete.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14065][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34654]\nTo complete this quest, simply head out to one of the Bountiful Tables (see the locations above) and sample five helpings of each of the five available foods. Doing so will grant you the [spell=61849 buff=true] buff required for this quest.[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[b]Cooking Quests[/b]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=14037][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34677]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34768]\nCook and bring 5 [item=44837] to [npc=34768] in [zone=1497]''s courtyard (the Ruins of Lordaeron). Don''t forget to make sure you have learned the [spell=37836] non-seasonal recipe.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14040][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34768]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34679]\nCook and bring 5 pieces of [item=44836] to [npc=34679] outside of [zone=1637]. While you are still in [zone=85], be sure to purchase [item=46796] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1497].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14041][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34679]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34678]\nCook and bring 5 servings of [item=44840] to [npc=34678] outside of [zone=1638]. While you are still in [zone=14], be sure to purchase [item=46793] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1637].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14043][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34678]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34679]\nCook and bring 5 [item=44839] to [npc=34679] outside of [zone=1637]. While you are still in [zone=215], be sure to purchase [item=46797] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1638].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14044][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34679]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34677]\nCook and bring 5 [item=44837] and 5 [item=44840] to [npc=34677] in [zone=1497]''s courtyard (the Ruins of Lordaeron). While you are still in [zone=85], be sure to head out and hunt down some [npc=32820] for the 5 [item=44834] the next quest will require.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14047][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34677]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34679]\nCook and bring 5 [item=44838] to [npc=34679] outside of [zone=1637]. The [item=44834] is dropped by the (appropriately named) [npc=32820] that can be found in [zone=85] (and [zone=12]). Upon turning the quest in, you will be rewarded with a [item=44844], which can be used to mimic a turkey mating call and summon a [npc=32820] to your side from anywhere. It is worth mentioning that killing this turkey does not count towards [achievement=3578].[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[b]Daily Quests[/b]\nEach of the cooking daily quests are fairly straightforward - simply get the required food, and bring it to the designated person - so they shouldn''t need extremely detailed descriptions. A book containing all of the new recipes can be purchased from a Pilgrim''s Bounty Vendor located near the major cities'' Bountiful Tables. Please refer to the recipes section above for detailed ingredients.\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=14062][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34713]\nCook (or buy) and bring 20 [item=44837] to [npc=34713] outside of [zone=1637]. Don''t forget to make sure you have learned the [spell=37836] non-seasonal recipe.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14060][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34714]\nCook (or buy) and bring 20 pieces of [item=44836] to [npc=34714] outside of [zone=1638]. You will have to go to [zone=85] to purchase [item=46796] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1497].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14059][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34712]\nCook (or buy) and bring 20 servings of [item=44840] to [npc=34712] in [zone=1497]''s courtyard (the Ruins of Lordaeron). You will have to go to [zone=14] to purchase [item=46793] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1637].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14058][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34768]\nCook (or buy) and bring 20 [item=44839] to [npc=34768] in [zone=1497]''s courtyard (the Ruins of Lordaeron). You will have to go to [zone=215] to purchase [item=46797] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1638].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14061][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34713]\nCook (or buy) and bring 20 [item=44838] to [npc=34713] outside of [zone=1637]. You will need to hunt [npc=32820] in [zone=85] (or [zone=12]) for the required [item=44834] meat.[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n\n[h3][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon] Quests[/h3]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=14022][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] Commoners, probably.\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34675]\nThis is simply a breadcrumb quest that leads you to out to the Pilgrim''s Bounty celebrations at the gates of [zone=1519], and is not necessary to be completed in order to obtain the other quests. Simply head out that way and talk to Gregory Tabor to complete.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14064][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34654]\nTo complete this quest, simply head out to one of the Bountiful Tables (see the locations above) and sample five samples of each of the five available foods. Doing so will grant you the [spell=61849 buff=true] buff required for this quest.[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[b]Cooking Quests[/b]\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=14023][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34675]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34744]\nCook and bring 5 [item=44837] to [npc=34744] at the gates of [zone=1519]. Don''t forget to make sure you have learned the [spell=37836] non-seasonal recipe.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14024][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34744]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34644]\nCook and bring 5 pieces of [item=44836] to [npc=34644] outside of [zone=1537]. While you are still in [zone=12], be sure to purchase [item=46784] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1519].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14028][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34644]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34744]\nCook and bring 5 servings of [item=44840] to [npc=34744] at the gates of [zone=1519]. While you are still in [zone=1], be sure to purchase [item=44854] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1537].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14030][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34744]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34676]\nCook and bring 5 [item=44837] and 5 [item=44840] to [npc=34676] at [zone=1657]. While you are still in [zone=141], be sure to purchase [item=44855] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1657].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14033][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34676]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34675]\nCook and bring 5 [item=44839] to [npc=34675] at the gates of [zone=1519]. While you are still in [zone=12], be sure to head out and hunt down some [npc=32820] for the 5 [item=44834] the next quest will require.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14035][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=34675]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=34676]\nCook and bring 5 [item=44838] to [npc=34676] at [zone=1657]. The [item=44834] is dropped by the (appropriately named) [npc=32820] that can be found in [zone=12] (and [zone=85]). Upon turning the quest in, you will be rewarded with a [item=44844], which can be used to mimic a turkey mating call and summon a [npc=32820] to your side from anywhere. It is worth mentioning that killing this turkey does not count towards [achievement=3578].[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[b]Daily Quests[/b]\nEach of the cooking daily quests are fairly straightforward - simply get the required food, and bring it to the designated person - so they shouldn''t need extremely detailed descriptions.  A book containing all of the new recipes can be purchased from a Pilgrim''s Bounty Vendor located near the major cities'' Bountiful Tables. Please refer to the recipes section above for detailed ingredients.\n[ul]\n[li][b][quest=14051][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34708]\nCook (or buy) and bring 20 [item=44837] to Caitrin Ironkettle outside of Ironforge. Don''t forget to make sure you have learned the [spell=37836] non-seasonal recipe.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14054][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34711]\nCook (or buy) and bring 20 pieces of [item=44836] to [npc=34711] outside of Darnassus. You will have to go to [zone=12] to purchase [item=46784] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1519].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14053][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] Ellen Moore\nCook (or buy) and bring 20 servings of [item=44840] to Ellen Moore at the gates of Stormwind City. You will have to go to [zone=1] to purchase [item=44854] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1537].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14055][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34744]\nCook (or buy) and bring 20 [item=44839] to [npc=34744] at the gates of [zone=1519]. You will have to go to [zone=141] to purchase [item=44855] from the Pilgrim''s Bounty vendor outside of [zone=1657].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][quest=14048][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [npc=34708]\nCook (or buy) and bring 20 [item=44838] to [npc=34708] outside of [zone=1537]. You will need to hunt [npc=32820] in [zone=12] (or [zone=85]) for the required [item=44834] meat.[pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h2]Achievements[/h2]\n\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/pilgrims-bounty/turkey.gif float=right border=0]Pilgrim''s Bounty features [b]nine[/b] unique achievements that can be earned! While it is definitely worth noting that the [achievement=3478] meta-achievement is [b]not[/b] required for [achievement=2145], this achievement awards not only a new player title but a non-combat pet as well!\n\nThat''s right, complete all of the Pilgrim''s Bounty achievements and your character will gain the title [b][i]''the Pilgrim''[/i][/b] and receive a [spell=61773] pet! Unlike that bony little brat from [event=51], this is a permanent pet.\n\n[ul]\n[li][icon name=side_horde][b][achievement=3656][/b][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][b][achievement=3478][/b][/icon]\nThis achievement requires you to complete ALL of the Pilgrim''s Bounty achievements, and will reward you with a new in-game title - [b]the Pilgrim[/b]! You will also receive a new companion, the Plump Turkey Pet! Once again worth mentioning, this holiday and its related achievements are [b]not required[/b] for [achievement=2145].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=3579][/b]\n[small][b]Bounce food off a fellow feaster''s head at a Bountiful Table.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must seat yourself at one of the Bountiful Tables (locations can be found above) and share food until you "miss" and end up bouncing the food off another player''s head! Players are reporting that this will happen when the player the food was getting passed to already had a maximum of the food, so just sit at any chair and pass food between players until you have earned this achievement.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][icon name=side_horde][b][achievement=3577][/b][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][b][achievement=3576][/b][/icon]\n[small][b]Cook up one of every Pilgrim''s Bounty dish.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must cook one of each of the listed Pilgrim''s Bounty dishes. These recipes can be learned from [icon name=side_horde][npc=34677][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=34675][/icon] and the reagents to cook these new recipes can be purchased from any Pilgrim''s Bounty Vendor. You will need at least [b]330 Cooking Skill[/b] to cook all five dishes. \n\n[pad]\n[table width=70%]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [b][icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon] Recipes[/b] [/td] [td] [b][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon] Recipes[/b] [/td][/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [spell=66034] [/td] [td] [spell=62051] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [spell=66035] [/td] [td] [spell=62049] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [spell=66036] [/td] [td] [spell=62044] [/td][/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [spell=66037] [/td] [td] [spell=62045] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [spell=66038] [/td] [td] [spell=62050] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[/table]\n[pad]\n\nCooking all five [icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon] recipes will require: 5 [item=44853], 3 [item=44835], [item=46797], [item=46793], [item=46796], [item=44834], [item=30817], [item=2678]\nCooking all five [icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon] recipes will require: 5 [item=44853], 3 [item=44835], [item=44855], [item=44854], [item=46784], [item=44834], [item=30817], [item=2678]\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][icon name=side_horde][b][achievement=3557][/b][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][b][achievement=3556][/b][/icon]\n[small][b]Acquire [spell=61849 buff=true] from a complete Bountiful Table feast at every Horde or Alliance capital.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must have a complete meal at each major city''s Bountiful Table, which means sitting in each of the five chairs to eat its provided dish. When you have sampled five helpings of each of the foods the table provides, you will gain the [spell=61849] buff which increases your reputation gain by 10% for an hour. Simply travel to each of your faction''s four major cities and sample five helpings of each of the five foods at its table to gain the buff.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][icon name=side_horde][b][achievement=3581][/b][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][b][achievement=3580][/b][/icon]\n[small][b]While wearing either a Pilgrim''s Dress, Robe, or Attire, take a seat at each enemy capital''s Bountiful Table.[/b][/small]\nThis achievement requires you to obtain an article of Pilgrim clothing from one of the Pilgrim''s Bounty daily quests (see above) and wear it as you visit (and somehow manage to seat yourself at) the Bountiful Tables in your opposing faction''s major cities. This achievement, similar to the [event=1] fire-stealing quests, may prove to be a huge pain on heavily populated servers, so it may be best to try this one during your server''s "off-hours" to avoid PVP complications.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][icon name=side_horde][b][achievement=3597][/b][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][b][achievement=3596][/b][/icon]\n[small][b]Complete each of the Pilgrim''s Bounty dailies.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must complete each Pilgrim''s Bounty daily quest. You can get each of the five daily quests from their respective questgivers at your faction''s classic major cities'' Pilgrim''s Bounty camps, and all five are available to complete every day.\n\n[pad]\n[table width=70%]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [b][icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon] Dailies[/b] [/td] [td] [b][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon] Dailies[/b] [/td] [/td][/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [quest=14061] [/td] [td] [quest=14048] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [quest=14062] [/td] [td] [quest=14051] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [quest=14060] [/td] [td] [quest=14054] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [quest=14058] [/td] [td] [quest=14055] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [quest=14059] [/td] [td] [quest=14053] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[/table]\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=3558][/b]\n[small][b]Pass one of every dish at a Bountiful Table.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, just sit at a Bountiful Table in each of the different chairs and pass the food to another seated player. The table chairs work similar to a vehicle, so you will have new abilities on your action bar to eat, pass, etc. Sit at all five chairs and pass it''s offered dish to earn the achievement! And remember - no hoarding the pie chair! We all like pie![pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=3582][/b]\n[small][b]Defeat Talon King Ikiss while wearing a Pilgrim''s Hat and either a Pilgrim''s Dress, Robe, or Attire.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement you will need to first obtain both a Pilgrim''s Hat and a seasonal chestpiece from the Pilgrim''s Bounty daily quests. You must then head out to [zone=3519]''s Auchindoun, and venture into [zone=3791] to defeat [npc=18473] while wearing your seasonal attire. This can be completed on either Normal or Heroic difficulty, in case you were interested in taking a druid along with the ability to summon [npc=23035] you can easily do both at once and maybe get lucky! Please note that you will, of course, have to be high enough level to zone into [zone=3791] (level 55) to complete this achievement.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=3578][/b]\n[small][b]Hunt enough Wild Turkeys quickly enough to gain Turkey Triumph.[/b][/small]\nThis achievement requires you to kill 40 [npc=32820], no more than 30 seconds apart per kill, until you have obtained Turkey Triumph (which is a buff, I''d assume)! [npc=32820], neutral critters, can be found in [zone=85] or [zone=12], and you can choose to kill them in either zone, though I don''t think subjecting yourself to PVP while trying to accumulate a stacking kill count is a very good idea. Expect this achievement to be a complete pain during your server''s peak hours, so this may end up being another one to save till the wee hours of the morning!\n\n[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=3559][/b]\n[small][b]Blast those dirty, sneaking Rogues with your [item=44812].[/b][/small]\nThis achievement requires you to use your trusty [item=44812] on a [color=c4][icon name=class_rogue]Rogue[/icon][/color] player of each race - transforming them into a turkey! Poor rogues! A [item=44812] can be obtained from Pilgrim''s Bounty daily quests, and can be used anywhere (so no, you won''t have to go to a battleground to try and complete this achievement), but it is consumed after a single use so you will need to keep doing dailies in order to complete the achievement. Make sure the player you use it on does not already have the buff, and is not in a vehicle, or it will consume the [item=44812] and not give you any credit!\n\n[pad]\n[table width=70%]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_bloodelf_male][icon name=achievement_character_bloodelf_female]Blood Elf Rogue[/icon][/icon] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_gnome_male][icon name=achievement_character_gnome_female]Gnome Rogue[/icon][/icon] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_troll_male][icon name=achievement_character_troll_female]Troll Rogue[/icon][/icon] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_nightelf_male][icon name=achievement_character_nightelf_female]Night Elf Rogue[/icon][/icon] [/td][/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_orc_male][icon name=achievement_character_orc_female]Orc Rogue[/icon][/icon] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_dwarf_male][icon name=achievement_character_dwarf_female]Dwarf Rogue[/icon][/icon] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_undead_male][icon name=achievement_character_undead_female]Undead Rogue[/icon][/icon] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_human_male][icon name=achievement_character_human_female]Human Rogue[/icon][/icon] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[/table]\n[pad]\n[pad][/li]\n[/ul]'),
    (300,9,0,'winter-veil','[menu tab=6 path=6,3,winter-veil]\n\n[div class="minibox minibox-left" style="text-align:left"][toc h3=false][/div]\n\n[div float=right]\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/winter-veil/tree.jpg border=0]\n[/div]\n\n[i]Deck the halls with boughs of [item=21213], and have a merry [url=/?event=141]Winter Veil[/url]!  It''s that time of year again, when kids run playfully through the streets tossing [item=17202]s at one another, old friends will gather to exchange gifts, and the fine gentlegoblins of [url=/?search=Smokywood+Pastures#npcs]Smokywood Pastures[/url] come once again to bless us with their delightful yearly gift packages (and fruitcake).  Cheers![/i]\n\nThis holiday can be celebrated by [icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon] in [zone=1537] and by [icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon] in [zone=1637]. Seasonal decorations such as holiday trees, wreaths and lights can be found in all major cities and at most zone inns. I''d assume that this year they have added additional holiday-related vendors / NPCs  in [zone=4395], so be sure to check the guide for updated info as it becomes available!\n\n[h2 clear=right]Quests[/h2]\n\nThe 2009 Winter Veil does not introduce any new quests, daily or otherwise, from 2008''s holiday. Even if you''ve done the quests in the previous year, be prepared to do them all over again in order to obtain any quest-related achievements (which are detailed below) or to obtain a different reward from the [item=17726].\n\nAll Winter Veil quests can be obtained in your faction''s major city ([zone=1637] or [zone=1537]). Other than start/end NPCs, the quests are essentially exactly the same for both factions.\n\n[ul]\n[li][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/winter-veil/santa.jpg border=0 float=right][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=6961][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=7022][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=13418][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=13434][/icon]\n[b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=13445][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=13444][/icon]\nThis quest''s objective is pretty self-explanitory - simply obtain the quest from the Smokywoods Pasture vendor in any major Horde or Alliance city (except Darnassus) and head to your faction''s major city to complete it. Horde players turn the quest in to the orc [npc=13445] in [zone=1637], and Alliance players to the dwarf [npc=13444] in [zone=1537]. A new quest will become available:\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=6962][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=7025][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=13445][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=13444][/icon]\nAnother pretty simple quest provided you''ve trained Cooking and don''t mind grabbing the materials for the [item=17197] - just bring him 5 cookies and a glass of [item=1179] (which can be bought from [url=/?item=1179#sold-by]vendors[/url]). As a reward, you will be given a [item=17727] which contains some [url=/?item=17727#contains]low level tradeskill materials[/url], so it''s up to you whether its worth your time to give the man his cookies and milk![pad][/li]\n[/ul][/li]\n[li][hr][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=6963][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=7042][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=13418][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=13434][/icon]\n[b]End:[/b] [npc=13636]\nThis quest asks you to travel out to the [zone=36] to find a missing Smokywood Pastures investigator who was sent out to search for a missing shipment of treats. Why you''d ship something taking a route that travels through the Alterac Mountains is beyond me, but whatever. Anyway, just head out to Alterac Mountains and search for the [npc=13636] [35,72]. Upon discovering his location, he will give you another quest:\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=6983][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=7043][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [npc=13636]\n[screenshot id=66118 width=558 height=674 float=right][/screenshot][b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=13418][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=13433][/icon]\nTurns out that the [npc=13602] has stolen the treats! Slay him and retrieve the [item=17662] so that the Smokywood Pastures guys can get on with their moneygrub.. er, holiday festivities! The Greench has about a 5 minute spawn, and will probably be heavily camped for the first couple days of the festival, so it''s best to group up with nearby players so you can get him killed and get out of there quickly. Once you have turned in the [item=17662], you will receive another quest:\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=6984][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=7045][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=13418][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=13433][/icon]\n[b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=13445][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=13444][/icon]\nSimply speak to the Great(-)father and claim your reward! You will receive a [item=17726] which contains a seasonal tradeskill recipe! This is the only way you can get these recipes, and the recipe you receive is [b]random[/b] so you may be able to trade with other players or guildmates for one you might need. If you don''t get the recipe you want, you can always check the Auction House or wait until next year.\n[pad]\nOpen the special gift to get one of the following recipes at random:\n[ul]\n[li][item=17709] [small](Alchemy)[/small][/li]\n[li][item=17706] [small](Blacksmithing)[/small][/li]\n[li][item=17725] [small](Enchanting)[/small][/li]\n[li][item=17720] [small](Engineering)[/small][/li]\n[li][item=17722] [small](Leatherworking)[/small][/li]\n[li][item=17724] [small](Tailoring)[/small][/li]\n[/ul]\n[pad][/li]\n[/ul][/li]\n[/ul][/li]\n[li][hr][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=6964][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=7062][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=9550][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=1365][/icon]\n[b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=13417][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=2916][/icon]\nThis short quest chain intends to explain the lore behind the Feast of Winter Veil. The questgiver is located near the bank in your faction''s major city, and he will send you to another NPC located within that city. Once there, you will receive a new quest:\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=7061][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=7063][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=13417][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=2916][/icon]\n[b]End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=3057][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=2784][/icon]\nThe questgiver will give you a book entitled [item=17735] to read, which contains some insight into the different races'' celebrations of the holiday. Once you have read the book (although, reading it isn''t actually an objective) you are asked to bring it to either [npc=3057] in Thunder Bluff or [npc=2784] in Ironforge, who will reward you with 500 reputation with their respective city and 125 with each other faction city - a considerable amount of reputation![pad][/li]\n[/ul][/li]\n[li][hr][b][icon name=side_horde][quest=8746][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=8762][/icon][/b]\n[b]Start & End:[/b] [icon name=side_horde][npc=13418][/icon] or [icon name=side_alliance][npc=13434][/icon]\n[screenshot id=66084 width=547 height=606 float=right][/screenshot]This quest sends you on a mission to rescue [npc=15664] who has been stolen and held for ransom! Apparently these Smokywood guys have made a lot of enemies in their day. Metzen can be found in two different locations; as specified in the [item=21314] he can be found at Lost Rigger Cove in [zone=440] and near the Stonewrought Gate of [zone=51]. You can complete this quest at either location, so just travel to wherever is most convenient. Once you''ve discovered Metzen''s location you only have to speak with the Reindeer to complete, you don''t physically [i]use[/i] the [item=21211]. Upon returning to the city, you will be rewarded a nice bit of goblin faction reputation and 5 [item=21213], which you can use year-round to turn your mount into a reindeer![pad][/li]\n[/ul]\n\nUpon completing [b][quest=8746][/b] a new quest will become available, [b][icon name=side_horde][quest=8799][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][quest=8763][/icon][/b] which asks you to bring [money=50000] and one [item=8150] to a Holly Preserver machine found in any city. As a "reward" you will receive 5 [item=21213] which do not have a duration and can be used at any time throughout the year. You can complete this quest only once, for a total of 10 Preserved Holly available from quests. These items can be used to temporarily change your ground or flying mount into a reindeer (yes, a flying reindeer)!\n\n[h2]Festivities[/h2]\n\n[screenshot id=66088 width=254 height=604 float=right][/screenshot]All of Azeroth and beyond have gotten into the spirit of Winter Veil! [url=/?npc=15760]Winter Revelers[/url] can be found inside inns throughout the world located under a sprig of mistletoe. Simply /kiss a Reveler (it doesn''t matter which gender) and you will be rewarded with a token of their gratitude! You can only /kiss a Reveler once every hour, as you will receive a debuff along with whatever gift they''ve granted you, which can include:\n[ul]\n[li][item=21519][/li]\n[li][item=21212][/li]\n[li][item=34191][/li]\n[/ul]\n\nThese items are used in various Winter Veil achievements (as detailed below).\n\n[h3]Become a Little Helper![/h3]\nIn addition to the Smokywood Pastures vendors located inside the cities, the goblins have set up strange PX-238 Winter Wondervolt machines which can be used to change your character into a festive Little Helper! The buff lasts for 30 minutes but is removed by shapeshifting or death (another sad holiday to be a druid). You can refresh the duration of the buff at any time by stepping into the Wintervolt machine. You can also do this to change gnomes costumes until you get one that you like. This disguise is required to complete the achievement [achievement=252].\n\n[h3][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/winter-veil/snow.jpg border=0 float=right]Snowball Fights[/h3]\nEveryone''s favorite annoyance (now knockdown-free, remember) the [item=17202] can now not only be purchased from [url=/?item=17202#sold-by]vendors[/url] but can also be looted from piles of [object=178609] found on the ground in the Alterac Mountains, near where you fight [npc=13602].\n\n[h3]Hunt a Winter Hat[/h3]\nDuring the Feast of Winter Veil, certain humanoid bosses now sport a festive holiday hat! The following Northrend bosses will drop a [item=21525] or [item=21524] upon their defeat:\n[ul]\n[li][npc=29310] in [zone=4494] - [item=21524][/li]\n[li][npc=27655] in [zone=4228] - [item=21525][/li]\n[li][npc=26731] in [zone=4120] - [item=21524][/li]\n[/ul]\nThe winter hats also have an extremely low chance to drop from any humanoid mob in the world; I wouldn''t hold your breath but who knows - you could get lucky! In previous years, Outland and Azerothian bosses would drop the hats as well, however in 2009 these hats will only drop from the Northrend bosses.\n\n[h3][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/winter-veil/gift.jpg border=0 float=right]Crafting Recipes[/h3]\nPlayers with Leatherworking, Tailoring or Cooking may find that they''ve received mail from Greatfather Winter written on festive stationary. Oddly enough, the Alliance Greatfather sends the gifts to both factions - a free recipe! Tailors will receive either [item=34261] (Horde) or [item=34319] (Alliance), Leatherworkers will receive [item=34262] and Cooks will recieve [item=34413]. There are certain skill level requirements for each recipe to be mailed, but if for any reason you did not receive a recipe, don''t worry - the recipes can be purchased at vendors in the major cities, as listed below.\n\n[h3]Gift-Giving[/h3]\nThe most exciting part of Winter Veil comes near the end - when we get our presents! The presents under Greatfather Winter''s tree can be opened from [b]December 25 to January 2[/b]. There are a total of six presents that can be "opened" by completing the quest given by the gift itself under the tree - [quest=8744], [quest=8803], [quest=8768], [quest=8767], [quest=8769] and [quest=11528]. Please note that the [item=34425] and [item=37710] obtained from the [item=34426] in previous years [b]will not be available[/b] in 2009, but instead a new item will be available from the Winter Veil Gift.\n\nEach of the gifts contain an assortment of special holiday items:\n[pad]\n[table class=grid]\n[tr] [td width=15%] [b][item=21363][/b] [/td] [td width=60%] [item=21328] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=15%] [b][item=21270][/b] [/td] [td width=60%] [item=21235] or [item=21241] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=15%] [b][item=21191][/b] [/td] [td width=60%] [item=21254] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=15%] [b][item=21327][/b] [/td] [td width=60%] [item=21213], [item=21325], [item=17720], [item=17725], [item=17722], [item=17709], [item=17724] or [item=17706] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=15%] [b][item=21310][/b] [/td] [td width=60%] [item=21301], [item=21308], [item=21305], [item=21309] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=15%] [b][item=46740] (Winter Veil Gift)[/b] [/td] [td width=60%] [item=46725] [/td] [/tr]\n[/table]\n\n[h2]Seasonal Goodies[/h2]\n\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/winter-veil/wreath.jpg border=0 float=right]There are a number of items that are only available during the Feast of Winter Veil. Smokeywood Pastures vendors can be found in all major cities selling a variety of holiday goodies, including a plethora of food and drink items, wrapping paper, and even some seasonal recipes! Please note that the three of the recipes are Bind on Pickup, and as such (of course) cannot be sold or traded. This means that it is not EASILY possible for Horde players to obtain [item=34319] or for Alliance players to obtain [item=34261].\n\n[i]However[/i], since the vendors are Smokywood Pastures "faction" they are all friendly to both Horde and Alliance, regardless of goblin or dwarf. This means that the most intrepid reveler [i]can[/i] manage to sneak into the opposing faction''s city and will be able to purchase the recipe from the vendor provided they can get the window open fast enough before suffering a painful, inevitable death.\n\nIf you aren''t a crafter or you''re not very keen on the idea of deathflopping around the other faction''s city, the holiday clothes are [b]not[/b] Bind on Pickup (or even Bind when Equipped) and therefore can be bought, sold and traded via the Auction House, so you could obtain the other faction''s winter clothes via the Neutral Auction House (for a price!).\n\n[h3]Food & Drinks[/h3]\nSmokeywood Pastures food and drink vendors can be found located near a faction''s Auction House in every major city. Copperpinch vendors can be found in Horde cities, and the Jinglepocket vendors can be found in Alliance cities. An additional Copperpinch vendor can be found in [zone=3703], [npc=23065].\n\n[ul]\n[li]Vendors found in [b][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon][/b] cities include [npc=13434], [npc=13436], [npc=23009].[/li]\n[li]Vendors found in [b][icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon][/b] cities include [npc=13418], [npc=13430], [npc=23011], and [npc=13431].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nThey sell the following items:\n[ul]\n[li][item=17404][/li]\n[li][item=17405][/li]\n[li][item=34412][/li]\n[li][item=17406][/li]\n[li][item=17407][/li]\n[li][item=17408][/li]\n[li][item=34410][/li]\n[li][item=17403][/li]\n[li][item=17402][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3][img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/winter-veil/stocking.jpg border=0 float=right]General Goods[/h3]Smokeywood Pastures "general goods"-style vendors can be found right next to the food/drink vendors. Copperpinch vendors can be found in Horde cities, and the Jinglepocket vendors can be found in Alliance cities (except Darnassus). An additional Jinglepocket vendor can be found in [zone=3703], [npc=23064].\n\n[ul]\n[li]Vendors found in [b][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon][/b] cities include [npc=13433], [npc=13435], [npc=23010].[/li]\n[li]Vendors found in [b][icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon][/b] cities include [npc=13420], [npc=23012], [npc=13432], [npc=13429].[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nThey sell the following items:\n[ul]\n[li][item=17202][/li]\n[li][item=17303][/li]\n[li][item=17304][/li]\n[li][item=17307][/li]\n[li][item=17194][/li]\n[li][item=17196][/li]\n[li][item=17344][/li]\n[li][item=17200][/li]\n[li][item=17201][/li]\n[li][item=34413][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h3]Patterns[/h3]\nIn addition to the seasonal goods listed above, the vendors located in the two major cities (Orgrimmar and Ironforge) will also sell a tailoring pattern to create festive winter clothes and a leatherworking pattern to create matching boots!\n\n[npc=13420] in Orgrimmar or [npc=13433] in Ironforge sell:\n[ul]\n[li][item=34261] ([small][icon name=side_horde]Horde[/icon])[/small][/li]\n[li][item=34319] ([small][icon name=side_alliance]Alliance[/icon])[/small][/li]\n[li][item=34262][/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[h2]Achievements[/h2]\n\n[img src=STATIC_URL/images/guide/winter-veil/reindeer.gif border=0 float=right]With each new event comes new achievements! The Feast of Winter Veil is no exception, with 13 different challenges for players and a new player title granted to those who can achieve them all - [i]Merrymaker[/i]! Some are easy, and others more of a challenge, but here''s everything you need to know to be on your way to becoming Merrymaker Corpsechewer or whoever you''ll be! :)\n\n[ul]\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1691][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1692][/icon][/b]\nThis achievement can be found in the main World Events achievement category and is awarded upon completion of all but one of the Winter Veil achievements. This achievement awards the player title ''Merrymaker'' and is a requirement towards completion of [achievement=2145] ([url=/?achievement=2144]Alliance version[/url]) which rewards the beautiful [spell=60024].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=4437][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=4436][/icon][/b]\n[small][b]Pelt the enemy leaders listed below.[/b][/small]\nThis achievement is new for 2009''s Winter Veil. For this achievement, you will have to use your newly acquired [item=46725] (obtained from the [color=q1]Winter Veil[/color] gift found under the tree) to pelt each of the opposing faction''s leaders - how mean! First snowballs, now BBs? What ever happened to respecting authority?[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=277][/b]\n[small][b]During the Feast of Winter Veil, wear 3 pieces of winter clothing and eat Graccu''s Mince Meat Fruitcake.[/b][/small]\nThis achievement [i]must[/i] be done during Winter Veil. You can wear any three pieces of the Winter Garb (a chest, boots and hat). The [item=34087] and [item=34085] can be crafted by Tailors, the [item=34086] can be crafted by Leatherworkers and the [item=21524] and [item=21525] are instance drops from three different bosses in Northrend instances (see above). The [item=21215] is contained within a gift package received within 24 hours of completing either [quest=6962] ([url=/?quest=7025]Alliance version[/url]) or [quest=8746] ([url=/?quest=8762]Alliance version[/url])![pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1690][/b]\n[small][b]During the Feast of Winter Veil, use your Winter Veil Disguise kit to become a snowman and then dance with another snowman in Dalaran.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievment, you must obtain and use a [item=17712] to become a snowman and /dance with another snowman in [zone=4395]. This achievement must be done during Winter Veil. The [item=17712] is obtained in the mail within 24 hours of completing the quest chain starting with [quest=6963] ([url=/?quest=7042]Alliance version[/url]).[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=1685][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1686][/icon][/b]\n[small][b]Use Mistletoe on the Horde/Alliance "Brothers" during the Feast of Winter Veil.[/b][/small]\nTo complete this achievement, Horde players must use [item=21519] on the following NPCs: [npc=5661] ([zone=1497]), [npc=26044] ([zone=3537]), [npc=31261] ([zone=210]). Alliance players must use Mistletoe on the following NPCs: [npc=1444], [npc=12336],  npc=5484], [npc=5489], [npc=1351] (all in [zone=1519]), [npc=739] ([zone=33]), [npc=927] (Goldshire, [zone=12]), [npc=1182] (Nijel''s Point, [zone=405]) and [npc=8140] (Theramore, [zone=15]). Mistletoe can be obtained randomly from /kiss''ing [url=/?npc=15760]Winter Revelers[/url].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1295][/b]\n[small][b]Gain 25 crashes with your Crashin'' Thrashin'' Racer during the Feast of Winter Veil.[/b][/small]\n[screenshot id=87208 width=512 height=353 float=right][/screenshot][i][b][color=q10]Warning:[/color][/b] This achievement is no longer required for [achievement=2145], as the [item=37710] was only available during 2008''s Winter Veil.[/i] This achievement requires you to have obtained the [item=37710] from the Winter Veil presents, available on and after December 25th. To complete this achievement you must "crash" 25 other racers. The controller functions similar to a [item=23767], only with a single ability: [spell=49297]! Out-slam another player''s Racer to earn a kill towards the achievement. You can battle against the same Racer multiple times to count towards this achievement, the car is (of course) not destroyed or damaged in any way and simply must be re-summoned.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1282][/b]\n[small][b]Complete the Bomb Them Again! quest while mounted on a flying reindeer during the Feast of Winter Veil.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you must be able to do the Sha''tari Skyguard quest [quest=11023]. Complete this quest while mounted on a flying reindeer during the Feast of Winter Veil. You can change your flying mount into a reindeer by using either [item=21212] or [item=21213], obtained from /kiss''ing [url=/?npc=15760]Winter Revelers[/url] or from quests detailed above, respectively.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1689][/b]\n[small][b]Open one of the presents underneath the Winter Veil tree once they are available.[/b][/small]\nThis achievement was awarded retroactively to players who had items or achievements related to any previous years'' gifts (such as the [achievement=1705] feat). To obtain this achievement, simply log in at any point from December 25th to January 2nd and obtain a gift from under the Winter Veil tree in either [zone=1637] or [zone=1537].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1687][/b]\n[small][b]During the Feast of Winter Veil, use a Handful of Snowflakes on each of the race/class combinations listed below.[/b][/small]\nDuring the Feast of Winter Veil, use a [item=34191] on the following race/class combinations:\n[table width=70%]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_orc_male][icon name=class_deathknight][color=c6]Orc Death Knight[/color][/icon][/icon][/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_tauren_male][icon name=class_shaman][color=c7]Tauren Shaman[/color][/icon][/icon] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_undead_male][icon name=class_rogue][color=c4]Undead Rogue[/color][/icon][/icon] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_gnome_male][icon name=class_mage][color=c8]Gnome Mage[/color][/icon][/icon] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_bloodelf_male][icon name=class_warlock][color=c9]Blood Elf Warlock[/color][/icon][/icon] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_human_male][icon name=class_warrior][color=c1]Human Warrior[/color][/icon][/icon] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_nightelf_male][icon name=class_druid][color=c11]Night Elf Druid[/color][/icon][/icon] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_troll_male][icon name=class_hunter][color=c3]Troll Hunter[/color][/icon][/icon] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[tr] [td width=5%] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_dwarf_male][icon name=class_paladin][color=c2]Dwarf Paladin[/color][/icon][/icon] [/td] [td] [icon name=achievement_character_draenei_male][icon name=class_priest][color=c5]Draenei Priest[/color][/icon][/icon] [/td] [/td] [/tr]\n[/table]\nSimply look around in any major faction city, [zone=4395] (especially!) or a battleground and you''ll probably end up with all of the combinations needed. [item=34191] can be obtained randomly from /kiss''ing [url=/?npc=15760]Winter Revelers[/url].[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=273][/b]\n[small][b]Save Metzen the Reindeer.[/b][/small]\nThis achievement is awarded upon completion of the quest [quest=8746] ([url=/?quest=8762]Alliance version[/url]). See the ''Quests'' section above for more information.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][icon name=side_horde][achievement=259][/icon][/b] or [b][icon name=side_alliance][achievement=1255][/icon][/b]\n[small][b]Throw a snowball at Cairne Bloodhoof / King Magni Bronzebeard during the Feast of Winter Veil.[/b][/small]\nBoth tauren and dwarf take Winter Veil very seriously, so what better way to show your complete lack of holiday cheer and respect than by smashing either [npc=3057] or [npc=2784] in the face with a [item=17202] during the Feast of Winter Veil.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=279][/b]\n[small][b]Complete the quest to retrieve Smokywood Pastures'' stolen treats and receive a Smokywood Pastures'' Thank You.[/b][/small]\nThis achievement is awarded upon completion of the quest chain starting with [quest=6963] ([url=/?quest=7042]Alliance version[/url]). See the ''Quests'' section above for more information.[pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=1688][/b]\n[small][b]During the Feast of Winter Veil, use your culinary expertise to produce a Gingerbread Cookie, Egg Nog and Hot Apple Cider.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement, you have to cook [item=17197], [item=17198] and [item=34411], the latter of which requires 325 Cooking skill. [item=17200] and [item=17201] can be purchased from Smokywood Pastures vendors, and [item=34413] can either be purchased or received as a gift from Greatfather Winter, provided you have high enough Cooking skill. Be prepared to grind your Cooking skill up if you haven''t already in order to get this achievement. [pad][/li]\n\n[li][b][achievement=252][/b]\n[small][b]Earn 50 honorable kills as a Little Helper from the Winter Wondervolt machine.[/b][/small]\nFor this achievement you must earn 50 honorable kills while transformed into a Little Helper from the Winter Wondervolt machine. Remember that the disguise is lost upon death or shapeshift, so this achievement might take a few tries to accomplish, but thankfully the killing blows are cumulative - just be ready to visit the Wondervolt between battles. Or simply be [i]awesome[/i]. I recommend [zone=2597] or [i]maybe[/i] [zone=4197], depending on the PVP situation on your server.[/li]\n[/ul]');
